title: sausage souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crust from bread.
Cut each slice into 5 fingers.
Place bread fingers over fruit.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and margarine.
Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, stirring well.
Store in tightly covered jar in a cool dry place.
To use, place 3 tablespoons of the mix in a cup.
Stir in small amount of boiling water to dissolve, then fill cup with water.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Saut ground beef in large Dutch oven until browned, stirring to separate. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until all vegetables are very tender. Any leftover meat, vegetables or pasta may be added, if desired.

title: pork chops in the skillet
directions: Season the chops with salt, pepper and cinnamon on both sides. In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Brown the chops for 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Add onions and carrots to skillet; reduce heat to low, cover and cook for 25 to 30 minutes until veggies are tender and chops cooked through.

title: ukrainian bread
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, orange peel and dry yeast.
Combine 1 cup milk, water and margarine in a saucepan and heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not have to melt completely.
Gradually add this mixture to dry ingredients and beat two minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 3/4 cup flour, beating at high speed for two minutes and scraping bowl periodically.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turning often to grease the entire dough.

title: made from scratch doughnuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry, then beat egg yolks one at a time.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Sift the flour and baking powder again.
Add alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring and the melted shortening.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut in doughnuts and fry in 380° oil.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; put in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Slowly stir in milk and cook until slightly thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour sauce over the macaroni and stir together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball on surface dusted with Bisquick.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes. Yields 9 to 12 buns.
(Double recipe for 18 to 24 buns.)

title: hot chicken enchilada soup
directions: Cut 6 tortillas into 1/2 inch strips and set aside. Cut remaining 6 tortillas into triangles and fry in hot oil until crisp; (or you may use corn chips) set aside. Saute onion and garlic in oil in dutch oven. Add next 11 ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour. Add tortilla strips and cheese. Simmer, uncovered 10 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with chips. Makes 8 cups.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear into bite sized pieces.
Toss apple wedges in lemon juice. Drain. Combine spinach, apple wedges, green onions and almonds; toss with bacon, if desired.
Combine oil and remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Before serving, pour dressing over spinach mixture; toss.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together; roll in 2 balls.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Sift together flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in butter.
Press this mixture into bottom of ungreased pan, 9 x 9-inch or 7 x 11-inch.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Fold in eggs, lightly beaten, and add cherries and coconut and nutmeats.
Spread this mixture over the bottom layer and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix and bake corn bread according to directions; remove from oven, cool and crumble.

title: cracker crumb chicken
directions: Wash chicken and press into cracker crumbs, coating well. Place chicken on a pan, sprayed with Mazola or nonstick spray. Salt and pepper chicken and sprinkle with water.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: hidden cheese briming
directions: Lay, evenly, 3 slices of cheese on half of the shell.
Fold shell over the cheese.
Put one cheese slice on bottom half of the folded shell and fold over.
Microwave for 1 minute.
It is yum-yum-yum-good!

title: eden isle chicken
directions: Pepper the chicken breasts.
Wrap one slice of bacon around each breast.
Place layer of dried beef in bottom of a greased baking dish.
Cover with mixture of chicken soup, sour cream and cream cheese.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well after each one.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.	Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
(I put flavoring in milk.)

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of bell peppers; remove insides and boil 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onions, shallots and minced garlic in butter.
Add meat and brown.
Shred moistened bread with fingers into skillet.
Add mushrooms and liquid, cheese, seasoning and bread crumbs.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, working quickly. Return to heat for 5 minutes.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix according to package directions.

title: chicken cleopatra
directions: *Add to own tastes.

title: meat loafettes
directions: Beat egg.
Add meat, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion, bread crumbs and vegetable soup.
Mix with a fork. Pam 12 muffin tins.
Spoon meat mixture into muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: blue cheese oven chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Dip in Blue cheese dressing.
Put bread crumbs in Ziploc bag; drop in a few pieces of chicken at a time and shake good to coat.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into chilled pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake 35 minutes or until set.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts if desired.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix together thoroughly the Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into walnut-size balls, dip into water and flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: russian cabbage soup
directions: Combine meats, vegetables and stock or water.
Add seasoning and simmer slowly for several hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat from soup.
Cut into slices and serve with soup. Garnish soup with sour cream.

title: 30-minute caramels
directions: Butter a 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.
In a heavy 4-quart saucepan, combine milk, corn syrup, sugars, butter and salt.
Place over medium heat and stir with a wooden spoon until mixture comes to a boil.
Clip on candy thermometer.
Stirring constantly to prevent scorching, cook to 240° or soft ball stage. Pour into prepared pan.
Cool at room temperature until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Optional:
Add 1 cup nuts before pouring into cooling pan.

title: pineapple grapefruit salad
directions: Soak gelatin in lemon juice.
Place drained pineapple juice on heat and bring to a boil.
Pour over lemon gelatin and plain gelatin.
Cool.
Add pineapple chunks, grapefruit sections and salt.
Pour into pans or molds and let set in refrigerator several hours.
Yields 12 to 18 servings.

title: baked pineapple(from 1975 edition)
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple and cheese.
In another bowl, mix flour and sugar and stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Do not grease Pyrex dish.
Put pineapple and cheese mixture in baking dish; pour the flour-sugar and juice mixture over this.
Cover with graham cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Good with most meats.

title: grandma's lo-cal dressing
directions: Mix together and store covered in refrigerator.
Keeps a long time.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix together margarine and cheese until well blended.
Mix in flour.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet.
Yields 10 to 12 dozen.

title: cyndie's artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar,
margarine and milk; bring to a rolling boil. Cook rapidly for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly (mixture burns easily).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer water, sugar and coffee 1 1/2 hours.
Do not boil. Cool mixture. Add vodka and vanilla.

title: mexican dip
directions: Add all together and put in a covered bowl in refrigerator for at least overnight.
Stir 3 or 4 times before serving.
This is better made the day before to allow spices to blend.
This is great with chips or can be used as a relish-type dish, served with your other Mexican dishes.

title: apple cake slices
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, vanilla, Crisco, baking powder and eggs.
Place half the dough in bottom of a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and put over dough.
Top with the remaining half of the first mixture.
Cut several slits on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Bring to a full boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove; add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well; drop by spoon on wax paper and let cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: shaker spoon bread
directions: Scald milk and add corn meal gradually.
Cook until thick. Pour small amount over beaten egg yolks.
Return to heat and cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter and fold in beaten egg whites. Add baking powder and salt.
Pour into greased baking dish and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once after first 15 minutes of baking.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook by spoonfuls in heavy skillet in hot fat. Serve with applesauce.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell. Bake 10 minutes in hot (425°) oven.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: grape ice cream soda
directions: Put in glass 2 scoops ice cream.
Fill glass with grape soda.

title: potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes; add chopped onions, pickles and boiled eggs. Toss with fork to mix.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Pour mixture over potatoes.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to flour mixture stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.

title: portuguese pickled onions
directions: Put vinegar, salt, chili peppers and garlic salt (or garlic which has been put through a press) in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put cleaned vegetables (cut in chunks) in a sterilized quart jar.
Pour boiling liquid over vegetables, seal, let cool and refrigerate.
This is a fast pickling method and the pickles are ready in 24 hours.

title: vinnie's shredded barbecue beef
directions: Cut roast in half or put in crock-pot whole.
Mix ingredients. Pour over meat.
Cook 8 to 10 hours, breaking meat apart after 5 hours and every hour thereafter.
Shred meat with a potato masher and then cook 1/2 hour more.
Serve on buns or rolls.
Times may vary upon meat breaking up.

title: pecan pie(my mother's!)
directions: Mix all ingredients (in order) by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler with soup and milk.
Put all other ingredients together with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs and slivered almonds.

title: dad's punch recipe(heritage recipe)
directions: Makes 6 gal., 30 to 35 c. per gal.

title: grandma fodroczi's yellow squash
directions: Add 1 teaspoon salt to 1 1/2 cups water and boil in medium pot.
Add squash, onion and garlic.
Boil for 35 to 40 minutes (or until soft).
Drain water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle 1/8 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes.
Let cool.
Add 1 cup sour cream.
Warm up to serve.
Serves approximately 4.

title: lentil peasant soup
directions: Place all ingredients except vinegar, salt and pepper
in soup pot and simmer covered for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the cider vinegar; season with salt and pepper.
Thin with water or chicken broth as desired.

title: whipped hot chocolate drink
directions: Heat milk on stove.
Pour hot milk into blender and add remaining ingredients and whip for approximately 15 seconds.
Pour into mugs to serve.
May use either marshmallows or Cool Whip to garnish.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large mixing bowl.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Put all mixed ingredients into baking dish.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top after margarine is put on. Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover.
Let brown, if desired.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: cranberry tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups of boiling water.
Boil 2 more cups of water with 1 cup of sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves for 10 minutes.
Add to tea, then add orange juice, lemonade and cranberry juice.
Refrigerate to serve.
Mix with equal part water and heat.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice with butter in skillet, stirring continuously. Place
in
1/2-quart casserole dish with the 2 cans of soup, undiluted.
Add
mushrooms.
Bake,
uncovered,
about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In a pie plate, dip chicken into egg. Coat with bread crumbs. In skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; keep warm.
In the same skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cookie salad
directions: Line a large bowl with cookies.
Layer with strawberries. Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Slice bananas over strawberries.
Pour Jell-O over layers of cookies, strawberries and bananas.
Chill until firm.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: In large saucepan, combine cream, butter and salt. Cook and stir over medium heat until butter is melted. Place potatoes in a greased 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish. Pour cream over potatoes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until potatoes are tender and top is golden brown. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired. Yields 12 servings.

title: easy chocolate nut crunch
directions: Sprinkle nuts over bottom of greased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Combine sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly, 4 to 5 minutes or to 270°.
Pour over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cover for a few minutes, then evenly spread melted chocolate chips.
Chill.
Remove from pan, break into pieces.

title: pizza rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornflake butter scotchies(an easy recipe that you can do with your kids.)
directions: Warm peanut butter and butterscotch chips in microwave until melted.
Stir in cornflakes until they are thoroughly coated with butterscotch mixture.
Place tablespoon of coated cornflakes on waxed paper.
Cool about an hour.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Roll chicken, cheese and a spoonful of sour cream in tortilla. Place each enchilada in oblong pan.
Mix soup and rest of sour cream, chilies and olives; pour over top.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until heated through.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans & eggs
directions: Heat green beans in skillet.
Add margarine, heat until melted. Stir in beaten eggs and mushrooms.
Fry over medium heat until eggs are set.
Add salt and pepper.
Very Tasty!!

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese and eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of 24 aluminum foil cupcake papers.
Divide cream cheese mixture evenly in 24 cups. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple cake
directions: Dice and peel apples.
Add sugar and let stand 15 minutes. Pour in oil and egg.
Stir.
Sift flour into apple mix.
Add cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Grease a square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: maple bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add egg yolk and beat.
Add flour and mix.
Add maple flavoring and vanilla; mix well.	Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 325° to 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips.
Place in oven for about 1 minute or until chocolate melts and can be spread.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix dry mustard and sugar.
Add vinegar and eggs.
Stir constantly on low heat until it comes to a slow boil.
Serve with bologna, cheese and pretzels.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup, unbeaten eggs, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat together well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: brazilian hot chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water in the top of a double boiler. Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and coffee.
Stir in 1/4 cup of the water and cook over direct heat 1/2 minute.
Add remaining water and milk; heat through and add vanilla.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: ideal brunch casserole
directions: In the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 inch pan, spread the croutons and cheddar cheese. In a bowl, beat eggs and milk with salt and mustard. Pour over the croutons and cheese. Sprinkle the crumbled bacon over the top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve hot. Can be made the night before and baked in the morning.

title: mary's turkey dressing
directions: Cook
chicken
parts
in plenty of broth.
Chop chicken and add to dressing mixture.
Add broth from chicken or turkey until dressing
is soupy.
Mix with your hands.
Spray baking pan or grease.
Bake until done at 350°.
If salt is added to chicken or turkey, don't add salt to dressing.
Best way is to taste it.

title: nita's wild turkey breast
directions: Deep fat fry.
Cut with grain, like steak finger strips.
Mix egg, flour, milk and salt together.
Batter and deep fry in Wesson oil or peanut oil.

title: corned beef luncheon salad
directions: Lime jello may be used.
Mold and cut thick slices.

title: layered rhubarb dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix 2 cups graham crackers with 1/2 cup margarine.
Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 5

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef in microwave-safe dish for 2 minutes; drain. Mix spaghetti sauce with beef.
Rinse jar with water.
Pour water in beef.
Mix egg with cottage cheese.
Mix pepper with cottage cheese and egg.
Put 1/2 of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Spread out. Put 3 or 4 raw noodles on top of this.
Then 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture.
Then put about a handful of Mozzarella cheese on this.
Put more sauce, 3 more noodles, more cheese and rest of sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High for 8 minutes, Medium-Low for 30 minutes.
Be sure all noodles are covered.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate rolls and place on 12-inch pizza pan, triangles toward center.
Press seams together.
Pinch up at sides.

title: espresso cheesecake
directions: In 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan, mix almond macaroons and butter; press on bottom and around side of pan to within 1 inch of top. Set aside.
(You can also use 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 2 teaspoons almond extract in place of the macaroons.)

title: non-alcoholic champagne punch
directions: Mix lemonade and grape juices.
Add ginger ale.
Pour into large punch bowl.
Add shaved ice or ice ring.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese should be soft.
Add Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Add green onions and beef; mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chicken
directions: Cut up and skin chicken.
Put all ingredients in electric skillet.
Cook at 200° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn once.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Put cherry pie filling in last and stir until mixed good.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood batter dip
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Add water and mix again. Dip fish or shrimp into batter. Drain off excess.
Fry in deep hot oil at 375° for 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Add sherbet if desired.

title: i-can-help orange balls
directions: Put wafers in plastic bag and crush using a rolling pin or a straight edge glass turned on its side.
This takes lots of energy!
Next mix in margarine with spoon.
Add xxx sugar minus 1/2 cup and orange juice. Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Put remaining xxx sugar in bowl and roll balls in sugar.
Eat and enjoy and be proud of you.

title: dakota spice cake
directions: Beat the egg and add the cream and continue beating.
Put dry ingredients into sifter and add alternately with molasses and sweet milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: layered turkey salad
directions: Place about 1/2 of the lettuce in a 5-quart glass bowl.
Top with a layer of beans, onion, turkey, zucchini, cheese, salami, remaining lettuce and tomatoes.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and horseradish; spread over tomatoes, sealing the edge of the bowl. Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: glazed chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine rice, boiling water and scallions. Mix well.

title: domino gingerbread men
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs and molasses.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough on well floured board until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.
Decorate with Sugar Icing as desired.
Makes 24 (5-inch) cookies.

title: eggs mornay
directions: Make a sauce with the first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Hard-cook eggs or cook less time, if preferred. Shell while warm and put in shallow baking dish.
Surround with the sauce and sprinkle with croutons.
Reheat if necessary in slow oven (300°).
Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: spicy sesame noodles
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and drain. Meantime, mix together all other ingredients, except scallions and red pepper flakes.
Add sauce to pasta and toss well.
Sprinkle with red pepper flakes and/or scallions if desired.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Place all ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Mix on medium speed of electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan; bake for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepot.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 half pints.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugars and vanilla together.
Beat eggs and mix with the creamed mixture.
Add flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until just tender; drain.
Combine carrots, onion and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients until completely blended. Pour over carrot mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: squash cheese casserole
directions: Mix together and top with bread crumbs (buttered).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk. Add extracts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hydrox mint dessert
directions: Put 3/4 of crumbs in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt marshmallows in 1 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside to cool.
Add peppermint flavoring and food coloring.
Fold in cream (or Cool Whip).
Pour over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top. Freeze and remove an hour before serving.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Place cookies 1/2-inch apart on pizza pan.
Bake using package directions.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in bowl until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Slice strawberries and mix with glaze.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and cool until serving time.

title: raisin cake
directions: First cream sugar and shortening together; then add eggs and beat.
Cook box of raisins in water until tender and have 1 cup of raisin water.
Then add soda to hot raisin water.
Add the raisins and water, spices, cocoa and flour.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 375° or until done.

title: buckeyes(chocolate covered peanut butter balls)
directions: Mix
peanut
butter,
sugar and butter in a large bowl. Roll into
small
balls.
Place	on wax papered cookie sheet. Freeze 1/2 hour.
Melt chips, Crisco and paraffin in a double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.

title: swiss eggs
directions: Stir eggs in pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread bacon or sausage over top, then cheese.
Drizzle milk over all.
Dot with butter.
This can be made up the night before and put into the refrigerator overnight.
Bring out and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be made in muffin tins for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen, brought out and heated in a 400° to 425° oven, preheated.
Heat 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with 4 or 5 strips of bacon. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: *Use 1/3 cup mild chilies for milder soup.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and add rest of ingredients, saving blueberries (do not use hand mixer). After batter is mixed well, then add blueberries.
Pour in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Make a layer of lettuce.
Mix onion and celery and sprinkle over lettuce.
Layer water chestnuts, then peas.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, layer remaining ingredients over mayonnaise.

title: garden cheese ball
directions: Press shredded carrot, zucchini and yellow squash between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine cheeses, grated onion and garlic in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Stir in shredded vegetables.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Shape chilled cheese mixture into a ball.
Combine cereal nuggets and parsley, stirring well.
Coat cheese ball with cereal mixture.
Wrap in wax paper and chill thoroughly.
Serve with unsalted crackers.
Yields 3 cups (23 calories per tablespoon).

title: tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in jar.
Use 1 teaspoon in cup of hot water.
Add sugar, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: orange cake
directions: Sift the flour with the baking powder.
Cream the margarine and sugar until pale and fluffy.
Add yolks one at a time.
Beat well between each addition.
Whisk egg whites until stiff; mix soda with orange juice.
Add orange juice to the margarine and sugar mixture, mixing well.
Alternate by adding to the margarine mixture a spoonful of flour and a spoonful of egg white, mixing well with a wooden spoon to avoid curdling.
Stir in the orange rind; pour into a greased pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for 45 minutes at 350° or for about an hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Pour hot water over raisins; cool.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, oil and pumpkin.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and spices. Add water, raisins and nuts last; mix well.
Batter will be thin. Pour into 2 small loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add well beaten eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Mix together.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch pans at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops n' vegetables
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chops, three at a time.
Brown well on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
Add green pepper. Saute 3 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Stir in flour; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Blend in next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boiling point.
Return chops to skillet; spoon sauce over chops.
Cover and simmer until chops are tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in tomatoes and sauteed green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: margo's vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix well and add 1 beaten egg.
Blend.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cooked, drained broccoli with cooked rice.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Place in slightly buttered casserole. Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: curried asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in shallow baking dish.
Mix 2 tablespoons margarine with bread crumbs and set aside.
Blend salt, pepper, flour and curry with remaining margarine.
Add milk and cook.
Add onion and pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with glass dipped in sugar.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; lower temperature to 325°.
Cook until firm.

title: mediterranean sausage bundles(makes about 40)
directions: Thaw pastry according to package instructions (approximately 20 minutes).
While pastry thaws, soak the tomatoes in boiling water to soften.
Cook the sausage, then cut into 1/2-inch slices. Cut these slices crosswise.
Quarter the tomatoes.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In a large, deep skillet, brown both sides of the chicken strips in butter or oil.
While the chicken is browning, add the mushrooms and onion.
When the chicken is fully cooked, stir in the soup, seasonings and milk.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in the sour cream and heat through.
Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour if placed in five (5) round cans or slightly longer if placed into two (2) loaf pans.

title: nebraska style baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Put into large baking dish and cover. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Uncover and cook for 30 minutes more.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti according to package; drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti until melted.
Stir in grated cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars and milk.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 5 minutes to 238°.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixture starts to lose its gloss.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cut when completely cooled.

title: four-cup hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together just before serving.
Add sliced bananas and/or apple chunks as desired.

title: chapati(indian wheat bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Place flours and salt in food processor bowl.
Turn on machine and slowly add yeast-water mixture.
Keep machine on until dough ball forms.
Place ball in greased bowl.
Cover with towel and let rise 1 hour in warm place.
Punch dough down and turn out on lightly floured surface.
Roll dough into a log about 1 1/2-inches thick. Cut into 12 pieces vertically.
Roll each piece into 6-inch circle.
In heavy skillet over high heat, cook one Chapati at a time, 1 to 2 minutes, until bubbles form.
With tongs, turn to other side, 1 to 2 minutes until golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook onions, pepper, celery and garlic in a separate pot until tender.
Add to meat with the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: c. a. t. toast
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Dip bread coating both sides well. Cook on grill or frying pan coated with vegetable spray.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all but butter; put into a 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Whip together sour cream, Philadelphia cream cheese and packet of taco mix.
Spread in pizza pan.
Spread jar of taco sauce on top.
Drop on lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In skillet over medium high heat, in hot oil, cook beef, garlic and onion until beef is browned.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce (mix together in a bowl before adding).
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: sauteed marinated hamburger steak dinner for two
directions: Marinate the 2 steaks for an hour with Dale's seasoning sauce. Grill steaks to person's preference.
Melt butter in a skillet. Mix mushrooms, onions, tomato and bell pepper and cook in skillet until onions are limp.
Best to cook on low-medium setting.
Pour ingredients evenly over the steaks and serve with side salad and baked potato or fries.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, over low heat.
Stir occasionally.
For crisp cabbage, cook 15 minutes.
For tender, cook 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In casserole dish, place a layer of tortilla chips and top with chicken breasts.
Cover with salsa and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (if using frozen, cook as directed on package).
Combine all other ingredients and simmer while broccoli is cooking.
Add broccoli and simmer for 20 more minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries, mash and strain.
Bring juice to boil; add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook 1 minute.
Cool.
Line baked pie shell with sliced strawberries.
Chill 2 hours in pie shell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add and mix milk and vanilla.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 16 to 18 muffins.

title: super broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, onions, raisins and nuts in large bowl.
Combine salad dressing and vinegar in a small jar.
Shake. Pour over broccoli mixture before serving.
For an interesting twist, add red seedless grapes, split in halves, to the mixture.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Heat enchilada sauce and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.

In a large round casserole dish; pour a small amount of sauce (just enough to coat the bottom) and layer 3 tortillas. Spoon in 1/3 of the ground beef, 1/3 of the onions and 1/4 of the cheese; cover with sauce.
Repeat twice, using all of the ground beef and onions and most of the cheese and sauce.
Top with the last 3 tortillas; cover with remaining sauce and top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in walnuts. In small bowl, beat eggs slightly, then beat in milk and vanilla, mix well.
Stir into flour mixture, just until moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling.
Makes approximately 24 servings.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popped corn and nuts on a cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, margarine and Karo syrup in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and nuts.
Mix to coat well.
Spread out to dry. Break apart and store in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, margarine, sour cream, soup and onion together.
Layer casserole dish with 1/2 of mixture and top with a cup of cheese.
Top again with mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and salt.
Drain fat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix hamburger and noodles together in large casserole dish.
Stir in creamed corn and oleo.
Salt and pepper to suit taste.
Bake in 350° oven until it bubbles.
Remove from oven.

title: breakfast tortillas
directions: Brown potatoes in oil in skillet.
Remove from pan.
Fry bacon or sausage (brown ham if desired).
Scramble eggs in skillet.
Add meat and potatoes to eggs.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste. In another skillet, heat tortillas, one at a time, in hot skillet. Take about 1 minute to heat both sides per tortilla.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Saute onion and celery in margarine in nonstick skillet until clear.
Mix broccoli, soup and cheese; add to celery and onion. Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Put into nonstick 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes and serve.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute chicken breasts in butter or oil until done.
Remove meat from bones, chop and set aside.
Chop together the cheese and onion in a food processor and mix with the chicken.
Fry the corn tortillas until soft and pliable.
Stuff tortillas with chicken mixture and roll them up.
Lay enchiladas in baking dish.
Make a roux with the butter and flour.
Add the chicken broth.
Boil until thickened.
Add the sour cream and chilies.
Heat until warm.
Pour sauce over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with picante, tomatillo or other sauce of your choice.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Freeze in small individual portions.
Remove from freezer 15
minutes before serving so that mixture will be slushy.

title: walnut or pecan pralines
directions: Break crackers apart and set side by side on cookie sheet. Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar and nuts, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Spread on crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: easy divinity
directions: Put marshmallow cream in a bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar, water and salt; bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 syrup into cream and beat well.
Pour 1/3 and beat well.
Add remaining 1/3 and beat.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat about 3 minutes.
Put on wax paper by spoonfuls immediately, as it gets hard fast.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat and onion until almost dry.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer until hot (about 5 minutes).
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in rice.
Stuff peppers; sprinkle tops with bread crumbs.
Fill baking dish with 1/2 inch water.
Place peppers in dish; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes, or until hot through.
Serves 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in a greased Bundt pan.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Cool.
Add fruit mixture, crushed crackers, vanilla, wine and a small amount of cherry juice.
Mix well. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Line Pyrex dish with wax paper and pack firmly in dish. Decorate top.
Place in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter middles
directions: Blend well peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into 30 (1-inch) balls.
Refrigerate.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Mix well.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in flour until blended.

title: circle cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening and add 3 cups sugar gradually.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating after each addition. Add plain flour to which baking powder has been added alternately with sweet milk.
Flavor with vanilla and lemon.
Pour in large steeple pan which is greased and bottom lined with wax paper. Place in cold oven at 350° and bake without opening door for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with graham crackers. Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on box for pie filling.
Pour slowly into cake pan.
Cover this with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Break cookies if necessary, but surface should be completely covered.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed, when finished cooking, ladle or pour slowly over layer of graham crackers.
Top with ground up crackers and chill at least 4 to 6 hours until set.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Place vegetables in 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes to partially thaw.
Stir in rice, soup, chicken, milk, half the cheese and the onion.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Make 3 wells and put in the next 3 ingredients.
Let set a few minutes, then pour the cold coffee over and mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2
cup sugar and cornstarch in 2 quart pan.
Stir in berries and water.	Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Boil and stir
one
minute.	Pour into ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Stir remaining ingredients until soft dough forms. Drop dough
by
tablespoons
onto hot berry mixture.	Bake until golden, about 15 minutes, at 425°.

title: fruity macaroon cookies
directions: In bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cookies cool on sheet 5 minutes before removing.
Cookies will be soft.

title: meribah clark's salad
directions: Mix and pour into a fancy mold.
Sets quickly.
Especially delicious in spring.

title: aunt kathy's buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and roll into small 1-inch balls.
Then in double boiler, melt chocolate chips and wax. Remove from heat and dip balls.
Let balls harden and enjoy.

title: portuguese rice
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in saucepan.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Layer in a casserole dish in this order:
1/2 of each Doritos, chicken and soup mixture; repeat. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Beat frozen lemonade into Eagle Brand milk until it thickens. Stir in Cool Whip.	Spread into pie shell and chill.
May be topped with a can of cherry pie filling or blueberry pie filling.

title: speedy pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in Pyrex; mix sugar, flour, milk together.
Add 2 cups fruit; pour mixture on butter.
Cook 40 minutes in slow oven (350°) or until golden brown.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain grease off.
Melt cheese and evaporated milk in microwave until smooth.
Add sausage.
Put in small crock-pot on low and use for dip.
Stir as not to stick.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Let
jello
start
to thicken;
beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in jello and stir until all is
well mixed.
Prepare in rectangular pan, 6 1/2 x 10 x 2-inch.

title: german pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening until mealy. In separate bowl, mix together water, egg and vinegar; add all at once to flour mixture. Mix with fork until pastry leaves the side of bowl. Roll out on floured board. Makes a flaky delicious, no fail crust! Yields 2 double crust pies and 1 pie shell, depending on the size of the pie plates used.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients, except Doritos and Longhorn cheese.
In a greased casserole dish, put a layer of crushed Doritos and a layer of chicken mixture, then sprinkle with grated Longhorn cheese. Repeat, ending with Doritos and cheese.
Refrigerate for an hour or overnight and then bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion in shortening in skillet. Add ground beef.
Cook until beef is brown, stirring frequently. Add salt, pepper, chili powder, tomato catsup, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add water as needed while chili cooks for desired consistency. Serve with rice or over hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix in pork and beans, tomatoes and salt.
Pour into greased casserole and bake about 1 hour in moderate oven.
May be topped with sliced bacon before baking.

title: north carolina syllabub(for tee-totalers)
directions: Chill ingredients and make shortly before ready to serve. Mix all ingredients except the cream, which should be beaten lightly.
Add cream and beat again.
Sprinkle the nutmeg on top and serve.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in an airtight container.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, crisco and flour. Add eggs one at a time. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for approx. 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Heat molasses and shortening together.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with ginger, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture.
Warm, mix and chill dough.
Toss on lightly floured board and roll very thin.
Cut in shapes.
Place on well-greased tin in moderate oven.
These are hard and snap.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and cut out top of bread. Fill with dip.
Use the bread you have removed as dippers.

title: drop filled date cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop from teaspoon on greased pan. Bake in hot oven. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: rich sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Blend together dry ingredients and stir with creamed mixture a little at a time.
Chill for several hours.
(If using a cookie press, do not chill and substitute shortening for butter.)
Roll out small portions to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutters.
If using pre-sifted flour, omit baking powder and salt. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with cookie crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: low-fat peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip using mixer until smooth.
Add sugar and peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box, adding pecans and bake as directed. After the cake cools, punch holes in it and pour the condensed milk and 1/2 jar of the topping over the cake. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Mix cut up candy bars with Cool Whip and frost.

title: nanny's yum yum chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix sour cream and soups.
Pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing. Melt margarine.
Combine with chicken broth and pour evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.
(Can use low-fat or nonfat sour cream.)

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: In small frying pan, saute onion and celery, chopped fine, until soft.
In another large frying pan, brown hamburg; drain grease.
Add mushroom soup, bouillon soup and 1 can water, along with onion and celery.
Simmer slowly for 1/2 hour.
Shut off heat; add sour cream.
Pour mixture over noodles.
It's oh, so good.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except stuffing crumbs and margarine.
Top casserole with crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper until smooth.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and salt.
Melt chocolate and
butter in a pan over hot water.
Combine sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Cream on "beat-whip" speed 1 1/2 minutes.
Add cooled chocolate and flour mixture. Blend in on "fold-blend",
then mix on "beat-whip" for 1 minute.
Stop to scrape bowl once.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or a 13 x 9
x 2-inch pan for thinner brownies.
Sprinkle nuts over top or beat into batter.
Bake about 25 minutes for square pan; 20 minutes for oblong. Cool in pan.
Frost, if desired.

title: port gravy
directions: Skim fat from roasting pan juices, reserving 1/4 cup fat, and deglaze pan with Port over moderately high heat, scraping up brown bits. Bring Port to a boil and remove pan from heat. In a saucepan, whisk together reserved fat and flour and whisk over moderately low heat for 3 minutes. Add Port mixture and stock/broth. Simmer and whisk for 10 minutes. Stir in lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Transfer gravy to a heated gravy boat. Garnish with fresh thyme, parsley sprigs and apple slices.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until creamy.
Add eggs; add flour alternately with milk and soda.
Add preserves and spices. Add raisins and nuts last that have been flavored.
Bake in four 8-inch layer pans in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal pie
directions: Stir all
ingredients
together.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
If you like, add pecans on top of pie before baking.

title: orange carrot salad
directions: Place carrots in a medium bowl.
Section oranges into the bowl to catch juices.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: green cake
directions: Mix together and bake as cake mix says.

title: quick brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir well.
Add remainder and mix well.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water (warm).
Stir in buttermilk mixture and yeast to dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Roll out and cut or just roll.
Dough will keep several weeks covered in refrigerator.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients by using your hands. Mix butter and cheese together, then add dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll into small balls and mash with a fork. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nacho potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine the potatoes and sauce mix, corn, tomatoes and water; mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add milk, cheese and hot pepper sauce if desired. Cook and stir until the cheese is melted. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, salt, vanilla, almond extract and syrup.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until filling is firm.
Makes 3 pies.

title: rice pudding
directions: This is a low-fat pudding.
Mix together in a 1-quart pan and simmer on low for 35 minutes.
Stir frequently.
May be served warm or cold.
If too thick, add more skim milk for desired consistency.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole. Place pineapple in a casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over the crumbs and bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Set potatoes and carrots aside.
Simmer all other ingredients for 1 1/2 hours; stir frequently.
The last half hour, add potatoes and carrots.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni with ham or chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook macaroni.
In large bowl combine all ingredients except cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover; bake 55 minutes.
Uncover; top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: curried shrimp appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Spread mixture onto bread and place under broiler 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Can freeze.

title: easter bread
directions: In small saucepan
heat
milk until bubbles form around edge. Remove from heat;
cool to lukewarm.
In large bowl add flour and make a well
in
center of bowl.
Place all ingredients in middle and begin mixing flour into center until all is mixed well.
Knead dough
on
a
lightly
floured board, until smooth.
Place in lightly
greased
large bowl.
Turn dough to bring up greased side.
Cover
with	towel
and
let rise in a warm place for 8 hours
or
until
doubled in size.	Cut dough into sections; place in
greased
bread
tins
and
let
rise again.
Brush top with
egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Add 1 carton sour cream last 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pot; heat over medium heat until it boils for 1 minute (stirring often and scraping).
Turn off heat.
Add the last 2 ingredients.
Stir well; drop onto buttered plates.

title: bean dip
directions: Alternate layers with Velveeta and Cheddar cheese in a crock-pot.
Makes a full crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cream and flavoring.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Let boil hard for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, stirring constantly until cool.
Spread on cake when cool.

title: rolls
directions: Set aside yeast cakes in 1/2 cup water.
Mix dry ingredients, then pour liquids.
Let stand about 2 hours.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease if any.
Add drained kidney beans, tomatoes and tomato juice.
Cook macaroni and add to the mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer on low for about 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: All ingredients are to be room temperature.

title: red carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until barely done.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
The longer everything marinates together, the better it tastes.
Serves a large group.

title: my own turkey salad
directions: Mix together and use.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in Pyrex or covered dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove lid and cover with French fried onions.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: italian pork sandwiches
directions: Heat grill. In medium bowl, combine pork, bread crumbs, onion, spaghetti sauce, basil and egg; mix well.
Shape into 6 oblong patties.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; stir.
Add water and vanilla.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with chocolate, baking powder and salt.
Add to the first mixture, stirring well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet, 3 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Good iced and sprinkled with chopped nuts.

title: firecracker barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over moderately high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and discard lemon slices.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cool to room temperature.
Can be refrigerated or placed in freezer in a tightly covered container.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix together and chill tomato, onion, garlic salt, celery salt and chili powder.
Just before serving, mash avocados and add lemon juice.
Combine and blend with chilled ingredients; check seasoning to suit taste.

title: liverwurst pate(don't tell guest what this is!)
directions: Mix all ingredients but save a little of cream cheese to mix with milk and spread over top of balls to form an icing and sprinkle with paprika.
To make ball, put 1/2 of mixture in Saran Wrap and form ball.
Chill.
Do same with rest of mixture.
Then ice top with cream cheese and milk.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Soak bread in cold milk; mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until brown on top.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out to about 7 x 11-inches. Cut out in 1/4-inch circles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: hungry man's hamburger casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and seasonings in baking dish.
Spread soup over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Tater Tots over top.
Return to oven and continue cooking for 30 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in deep pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and salt.
Distribute evenly over the melted oleo. Do not stir.
Mix fresh peaches with 1 cup sugar and let stand until sugar makes a syrup.
Spoon evenly over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until evenly browned. Batter will come to top.

title: cocoa souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 6-cup souffle dish with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Lightly dust with confectioners sugar.

title: mike's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together. Add shortening and blend. Add yeast and buttermilk; mix well. Store in icebox until needed. Bake on greased pan at 400° until brown.

title: pickled okra
directions: Mix and simmer for 10 minutes the vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Place washed okra in sterilized wide mouth jars with points of okra down.
Add dill weed, whole cloves, garlic and hot pepper. Pour hot vinegar mixture over okra and other ingredients in jar. Seal and let stand at least
a week before serving.

title: texas hash
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown steak in oil.
Remove meat. Brown the ground beef and sausage together, mixing well and crumbling fine.
Remove meat.
Add to the drippings in the Dutch oven the onions, green pepper, garlic and jalapeno pepper and saute until tender.
Add the browned meat and remaining ingredients.
Bring chili to boiling point, then cut back heat to very low or simmer and continue cooking for at least 4 hours.
The longer the chili sets, the more flavorous it becomes.

title: fisherman's casserole
directions: Peel, boil and mash potatoes.
Cook peas.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in oil for 5 minutes.
Brown lightly 2 tablespoons flour.
Combine the fried mixture with 1 1/2 cups water.
Turn mixture into 1-quart casserole.
Spoon potatoes in ring around edge of dish.
Put salmon in middle of ring.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute butter, peppers and onions.
Add mushrooms, pimentos, salt, garlic powder, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom. Combine chicken, spaghetti and sauce.
Mix well.
Pour into a large Pyrex.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: garlic broccoli and pasta
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet on top of stove.
Saute garlic in butter until lightly browned.
(At this point, begin heating water for pasta.
Prepare pasta as directed on box.)
Pour in chicken broth with garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Add broccoli flowerets.
Turn heat to simmer and cover.
Cook until broccoli is desired consistency.
When pasta and broccoli are done, combine the two in a large serving bowl and enjoy.

title: dip
directions: Combine and serve with crackers, bread sticks, etc.

title: white salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool in refrigerator.
Blend pineapple and cream cheese until smooth. Add to jello mixture; chill until slightly thickened, then fold in Cool Whip. Chill until firm. This keeps well for several days.

title: mexican pinto beans
directions: Wash beans. Add all ingredients. Cover with water and simmer 2 hours or until well done.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Put sliced strawberries in small bowl; add granulated sugar and set aside.
Break angel food cake into medium size pieces into large bowl.
Prepare jello as directed, leaving cool, but don't gel.
Add Cool Whip to jello; stir.
Pour this over cake and mix. Drain liquid off of strawberries into small saucepan; add strawberries to cake and mix lightly.
Pour cornstarch in liquid; stir until dissolved; put on low heat until thick as syrup and pour over cake mixture and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cream cheese and butter.
Beat together.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla extract.
Beat until smooth and set aside.
Mix cake like brownies as directed on package.
Pour half of brownie batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over the brownie layer.
Spoon remaining brownie batter in spots over the top.
Swirl the 2 mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool. Frost with milk chocolate frosting.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a bowl. Rinse the chicken wings and pat dry with paper towels. Add chicken to marinade and toss well. Let stand for 20 minutes at room temperature or refrigerate several hours or overnight. Place the oven rack 6 to 8-inches below heat source and preheat the broiler to high. Place the chicken on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray and spread out the chicken evenly. Broil about 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until thoroughly cooked. Serve hot with Blue cheese or Ranch dressing.

title: peaches with praline biscuits
directions: Roll up like a jelly roll and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place in baking dish on top of peach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in airtight storage container. Add 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water for tea.
(May substitute 5 packages Sweet 'N Low for sugar.)

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Let cool; cut into chunks.
Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add flour; stir well.
Add milk; let thicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in grated cheese until melted in mixture.
Blend in pimento.
Pour over the potatoes.

title: potato salad for a crowd
directions: Peel potatoes.

Slice half, dice the other half (the slices cook softer and give the finished salad a nice consistency). Rinse the raw potatoes under cold water until water runs clear. Cover with cold water; add about 1 teaspoon salt (more or less to taste) and cook until tender.
Remove from heat and pour cooked potatoes into a colander to drain.
When cool or lukewarm, add the remaining ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Use enough mayonnaise to moisten and amount to your taste.
When completely mixed, chill.

title: lentil stew
directions: Soak lentils overnight. Cut and dice ham.
Peel and dice potatoes and chop onion. Drain lentils and put in pot with all the other ingredients.
Cover with water and boil about 2 hours at medium heat.
Serve hot.

title: people chow
directions: After melting chocolate chips and butter together, mix in peanut butter.
When thoroughly mixed, add Bran Chex and carefully coat each Chex with mix.

title: virginia dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: jogging juice
directions: Drink 2 1/2 ounces per day.
Gives you energy and helps keep cholesterol level down.

title: cabbage carrot slaw
directions: In large bowl toss cabbage, carrot and onion. Mix oil, vinegar, salt, caraway and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and toss. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Place eggs in blender.
Add milk, flour, and salt; beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add salad oil; beat 1/2 minute. Grease muffin tins thoroughly.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake for 15 minutes until they rise and turn brown; turn down to 350° and bake 25 minutes.

title: miss jennies turkey dressing
directions: Crumble hush puppies and hamburger buns. Chop celery and onion. Add to bread mixture. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Add enough turkey broth to consistency. Dot with butter and black pepper. Cook at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Saute the onions until soft in the butter or margarine.
Brown the ground beef slightly; add salt and pepper.
Add the chili powder, parsley, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Add the cooked rice to the mixture; mix all together.
Dot top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour in a 300° oven.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Put fruit, cottage cheese and jello in bowl and fold.
Add Cool Whip and blend together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Cut tenderloins in half.
In shallow baking dish, combine all remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Place meat in mixture, turning it to soak on each side (at least 1 hour).
Cover with bacon slices and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 325°.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together; drain off excess fat. Mix together Ro-Tel, beans and soup.
In bottom of large casserole, put layer of tortillas (6).
Next put layer of bean mix, layer of hamburger
mix
and
layer
of cheese.
Continue until
all
ingredients
are used.
Place in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, eggs, butter and sour cream/soda mixture. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean.
Cook in Bundt pan.

title: white bread plus
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the 1/2 cup water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Beat in remaining ingredients, except flour.
Add flour gradually to desired consistency.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Knead on floured board for 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and knead 2 more minutes.
Shape into 3 or 4 loaves and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Brush with butter.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: fried trout
directions: Cut onion across; scrape off pulp.
Mix with lemon juice and salt.
Marinate fish thoroughly.
Make batter of egg whites, wine, sugar, salt, cayenne and ginger.
Beat as stiff as possible.
Roll fish carefully in batter.
Saute in butter 6 minutes on each side on low heat in skillet.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage for a couple of minutes in 2 tablespoons of water to soften.
Layer 1/2 of cabbage, sauce and crumbs in casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate crinkle
directions: Melt chocolate and mix with oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture.
Chill 2 hours and roll in balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 to 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan. Makes 4 dozen.

title: syrian salad
directions: Rub salad bowl with garlic.
Mix all dry ingredients and pour dressing over.
Marinate overnight.
Keeps 1 week.

title: french-onion dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: oven-fried chicken monterey
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup flour and the taco seasoning mix in a paper or plastic bag. Add 2 or 3 chicken pieces at a time and shake to coat. Melt butter or margarine in a 15 x 10 x 2 baking pan. Place chicken in pan, turning once to butter surfaces. Roll in crushed chips and return to baking pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Meanwhile, cook onion in oil until tender but not brown. Blend in the 2 tablespoons flour and the salt. Add evaporated milk. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add cheese and lemon juice, stirring until cheese melts. DO NOT BOIL.

title: fudge pie
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix with mixer at low speed.
Beat eggs and yolks together; add to cocoa mixture, then add milk.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Top with meringue made from the 4 egg whites.

title: lazy man's chili beans
directions: Mash garlic, salt and sugar to a paste.
Blend into chili. Fry bacon until golden; add onion and cook until soft and transparent.
Stir in kidney beans, water and chili mixture; simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
May be made day or so before and reheated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mary smith's crab cakes
directions: Fluff up crab meat.
Roll crackers on waxed paper.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into cakes.
Saute in margarine or butter.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Now add chilies, cheese and corn.
Sift and add flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Cook beans according to directions on package.
Combine into a large pan (do not pour off water).
Add green onions, crumbled dry cayenne peppers, stewed tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer for about 1 hour until water has cooked down.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Makes 4 cups.
Recipe may be cut in half or doubled.

title: chunky tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Cover and let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Grease and flour 9-inch spring-form pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese twice in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, 2 cups milk, mustard and onion.
Pour egg mixture over layered ingredients. Mix remaining 1/2 cup milk with soup and pour over top of casserole.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Mix well pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13 pan and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cream cheese and blend in 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread over pretzels mix.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put beans in bottom
of pan and sprinkle with taco mix. Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain
and	put on top of beans. Top with salsa sauce and
bake at 400° until hot.
Take out of oven and sprinkle cheese on	top
to
cover.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: mexican nut cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan; do not flour. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls. Roll each ball in coconut.

title: jeremiah's chicken
directions: In the oven, melt margarine in baking dish.
Roll chicken in butter and then in bread crumbs.
Wrap each chicken breast with one bacon slice.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Mash bananas thoroughly and combine with juices.
Combine sugar and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool completely and add to banana mixture.
Divide into three half gallon containers and freeze.
Two hours before serving, remove from freezer and add ginger ale and drained maraschino cherries.
Yields 50 cups.

title: choco-mint shake
directions: Microwave 1/2 cup milk for 1 minute, or until hot.
Pour into blender.
Add cocoa and mix until smooth.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture slowly.
Mix thoroughly. Add apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° in greased and lightly floured pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely in pan before trying to remove.

title: delightful fruit punch
directions: To make a syrup, boil sugar and 1 cup water.
Pour syrup over gelatin and dissolve.
Add juices and enough water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze.
On day of serving let thaw about 6 hours.
Serve as a slush.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce for first layer and add mango for second layer. For third layer, add onion.
Add peas for the fourth layer.
Top with mayonnaise for fifth layer and Cheddar cheese for sixth layer.
Put bacon on top for seventh layer.

title: yeast bread(four loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to scalded milk that has been cooled.
Combine dry ingredients and mix a little at a time until dough is not sticky.
Let rise for 60 minutes until bulk has doubled.
Bake in loaf pans for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: cauliflower morranco
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter with juice of 1 lemon. Saute cauliflower flowerets in butter with garlic, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients, put in greased casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookie
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins. Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: aunt adah's beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in diagonal strips.
Lightly flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add water, mushrooms (including liquid if canned).
Tougher cuts of meat will need to cook longer. Stir in soup mix and spices.
Heat just to boiling.
Blend sour cream in flour; add to liquid mixture and cook until thickened. Sauce will be thin.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serve baby green peas on the side and green salad.

title: spicy chile vinegar
directions: Poke into a bottle the bay leaves, hot red chilies and cloves of garlic.
Fill with red or white wine vinegar.

title: honey cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is fluffy.
Dilute honey with hot coffee and cool to lukewarm. Add oil.
Blend into eggs and sugar alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and fruits.
Blend, but do not overbeat. Pour into a well-greased and paper-lined pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour.
Invert on a rack to cool and cut into squares.

title: player's bread pudding
directions: Place crumbled bread in 9 x 12-inch greased casserole dish. Mix cream, milk, eggs, sugar and spices together with a wire whisk. Pour over bread and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs and margarine and pack in 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 10 minutes at 400°; cool.
Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour over pretzel crust and refrigerate.

title: quick cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Stir soups and milk together in medium saucepan until smooth.
Add broccoli and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil.
Add ground beef; cook slowly. Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and spices; continue cooking for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles and drain. Arrange in pans: layer of overlapping noodles, layer of meat sauce, Swiss or Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat noodles, meat, cheese and noodles; spoon remainder of meat sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice to package directions.
Add Cheez Whiz and undiluted soup.
Thaw broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients together and pour into an ungreased 8 inch square pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stewed chicken wings
directions: Cover the chicken wings with tomatoes and chicken stock or water.
Bring to a boil for about 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until wings are tender.
Serve with boiled rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pistachio salad
