directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple together (including syrup). Mix thoroughly and add Cool Whip; blend well.
Add marshmallows and fruit cocktail.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: fat-free pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Spray 9 inch square baking pan with cooking spray. In large bowl combine dry ingredients and raisins. In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Stir until smooth and then add to dry ingredients. Again stir until smooth. Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tester comes out clean.. Makes 16 servings.

title: sausage balls for soup
directions: Note:
Good in pea, bean or lentil soup.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Very Good!

title: shrimp and vegetable spaghetti
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the pasta, stirring once, until the spaghetti is tender, but still firm, about 8 minutes.
Drain immediately; rinse with cold water and drain again.
In a large skillet, melt the butter in the olive oil over moderately high heat.
Add the carrots and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add the red and green peppers and the garlic and cook, stirring, until slightly soft, about 3 minutes.
Stir in the squash and zucchini and cook until slightly soft, about 3 minutes longer.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the vegetables to a bowl. Add the shrimp to the hot skillet and saute for 1 minute.
Add the fish stock and cook, scraping the bottom and sides of the pan, about 30 seconds.
Add the cream and bring the liquid to a boil. Cook, stirring, until the shrimp are just cooked through, about 2 minutes longer.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Spread one side of bread slices well with butter.
Place, buttered side down, in glass baking dish.
Place ham and cheese on each slice. Cover with second bread slice, buttered side up.
Mix eggs, milk and salt (beat well).
Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add to soft cream cheese the dried beef, cut into small squares, thin sliced onion greens, minced garlic to taste and celery salt to taste.
Form into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: chicken salad ambrosia
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and Italian salad dressing mix. Pour over chicken and toss gently.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Arrange on lettuce and garnish with additional grapes.

title: venison roast
directions: Soak roast in 1/2 c. vinegar and 3 Tbsp. salt in enough water to cover roast for about 4 hours.
Remove and pat dry.
Rub roast with seasoning salt or Cajun seasoning.
Cut slits in roast and insert cloves of garlic.
Put olive oil in pan and heat.
Quickly sear outside of roast.
Remove from pan and place in aluminum foil and seal well.
Pour on liquid smoke and worcestershire sauce. Seal well in foil.
Place in pan and roast at
300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Check after 3 hours.
Don't overcook.
Do just past medium rare or medium.
Serve with dripping juice from pan and vegetables.

title: gertie's salad
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, juice and egg.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Let cool.
Cut marshmallows.
Add pineapple and mix.
Add cooked mixture to pineapple and marshmallows.
Add whipped cream to this mixture.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Stir all ingredients, except raisins, with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Bake until toothpick inserted comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides to loosen and remove from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: taco salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Then spread on a large round platter.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Put peaches into unbaked pie crust.
Beat the rest of the ingredients; pour over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top before baking.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and core the apples.
Place in baking dish in layers. On each layer put apples, sugar, dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the water to the dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put basil, garlic and pinenuts in a food processor and process to chop leaves somewhat.
Add olive oil and continue to process, scraping down sides of bowl. Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: plain dinner rolls
directions: In a saucepan, combine margarine and milk on low heat to a warm temperature.
Add sugar and salt; pour in mixing bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Gradually add enough flour that dough can be handled to knead on board.
Return to mixing bowl and cover; let rise until double in size.
Turn out on board and cut into dinner size rolls (pocket book roll).
Place on baking sheets and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until done. Brush with melted margarine.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter syrup cake
directions: Mix as any cake, bake in deep layer pan in moderate oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Break and serve hot.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil in bowl by hand.
Add unsweetened chocolate and mix thoroughly.
Add and mix in flour, then walnuts and vanilla.
Put mixture in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: hampton roads crab cakes
directions: In medium bowl mix
egg,
mayonnaise, green pepper, dry mustard and red pepper.
Beat with a wire whisk until blended. Gently fold in crabmeat so it
will
still be in chunks.
Pour some cracker meal on
wax
paper.
Form
patties
and
lightly bread before frying.
Cook until
golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 patties.

title: brown sugar stack cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add buttermilk with flour.
Bake at 450° for thin layers.
Put fruit between layers.

title: fiesta guacamole dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies.
Spread on large serving plate.

title: easy pigs in blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon over cabbage.

title: coffee butterball cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add confectioners sugar.
Cream until fluffy. Dissolve coffee and soda in water.
Add to butter mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: snack time peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix the margarine, white and brown sugars, egg and peanut butter together until creamy smooth.
Slowly add in the dry ingredients.
Mix well or until dough forms one large ball. Chill dough in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: fudge nut brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, combine brownie mix, flour, water, oil and egg.
By hand, stir with a spoon until dough is formed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet; cool completely.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
For a thicker cookie, add 2 to 4 tablespoons flour. Makes 3 dozen.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham and pork together.
Mix meat well.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with brown sugar and ground cloves.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: whipped cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Let chill for several hours before serving and the cool whip will thicken again.
Can be frozen and served like ice cream.
It will mix easier if you let the Cool Whip sit out a while to soften before stirring in other ingredients.

title: polish tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolk; mix well. Add flour, sifted with salt; mix.
Roll dough into small balls. Dip in unbeaten egg whites and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place on buttered baking sheet; press down center of each with thimble. Bake in a 325° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and press down again with thimble.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and fill indentation with preserves or melted chocolate while still warm.

title: heavenly hamburger bake
directions: Spread bread lightly with butter and arrange in bottom of eight-inch square baking dish.
Toast lightly in moderate oven. While bread is toasting, brown meat with onion and celery in butter or margarine.
Mix in mustard.
Spread meat mixture over toasted bread.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of meat.
Cover remaining bread slices to make sandwiches.
Combine eggs with milk and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
To make this even quicker; toast the bread lightly in the automatic toaster.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: farm butter
directions: Beat margarine and oil together.
Add buttermilk slowly and beat.
Put in containers and refrigerate.
This will stay soft in the refrigerator.
I also have frozen the butter.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and 1/4 cup of chopped pecans, sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Add 2 cups boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add crushed strawberries (frozen or fresh).
Stir until slightly thickened.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip with 1 cup sugar.
Cover cooled pretzel crust and jello mixture with cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup chopped pecans.

title: double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup chocolate bits and butter in a large saucepan over low heat. Stir until smooth. Remove from heat. Add eggs and stir well.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir well. Stir in remaining 1 cup chocolate bits and nuts. Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Thaw shrimp.
Chop celery and onion fine.
Shred lettuce. Combine shrimp, celery, onion and lettuce in bowl.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops
in
bottom
of
pan.	Add
a layer of potatoes, layer of onions and seasonings on top of pork chops. Add soup and 1 can of water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: sour cream-potato casserole
directions: Use instant potatoes if you don't have leftovers.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles using package directions.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise and onion.
Heat (stirring) soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and continue heating until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into a 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix sauerkraut, onion and sour cream.
Spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with the crumbled corned beef and then the Swiss cheese.
Top with the bread cubes which have been tossed with the melted butter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.
(Half recipe in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 35 minutes.)

title: baked eggs with herbs and vegetables
directions: Pre-heat the oven 350°F. Soak the saffron strands in 1 Tbsp. boiling water.

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend in blender or shake well.

title: roast beef sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish, with a lid, large enough for all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 6 hours.
Put on buns.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: In a bowl, combine pecans, coconut and butter. Pour onto an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Spread nuts in bottom of shell.
Pour filling on this. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake 25 minutes more.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Beat well.
Add vanilla and prunes.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in a 3 qt. saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour and spices; stir constantly and cook until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in lobster and juice.
Serve hot inside split popovers.

title: pistachio (watergate) salad
directions: Mix pudding with juice from pineapple; add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: old fashioned ginger bread
directions: *BLKLIN moves the ends.

title: jamaican gingerbread
directions: Sift ginger with the flour; add the peel and mix.
Heat sugar, butter and molasses over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Dissolve the soda in the milk; add the beaten eggs and beat a little more. Add molasses mixture and egg mixture to the flour, mixing thoroughly.

title: quick and easy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add brown sugar; cook and stir until sugar melts.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat in confectioners sugar until thick enough to spread.
This recipe makes enough to frost a 3-layer cake.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice off tops of peppers; take out seeds.
Place peppers in enough boiling water to cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Cook hamburger and onions until brown.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.
Fill peppers with stuffing.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: frozen dessert salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.
Serve and enjoy!
Serves 10 to 12.

title: potato candy fudge
directions: Boil potato until done.
Mash potato with a fork.
Add enough confectioners sugar to mashed potato until it forms a dough that can be rolled out with a rolling pin.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator to set up.
Take out when firm and whiz in blender until very smooth.
Pour in baked crust and put back in refrigerator; let set up until firm. Garnish with lemon twist and mint.
Contains 50 calories per serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple, Tang and instant pudding.
Stir and add bananas, pineapple and oranges.
Put in refrigerator.

title: florida calico scallops supreme
directions: Melt butter in baking pan while oven is preheating to 350°. Remove pan.
Place washed scallops in melted butter and top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Cook celery, onion and garlic in butter.
Add beef, tomatoes and seasonings and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
Arrange layers in greased baking dish:
first, a layer of noodles, then sauce, then alternating layers of cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining noodles and sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8!

title: gourmet onions vidalia onions
directions: Mix salt, sugar, pepper and m.s.g., if using.
Sprinkle over sliced onions.
Mix and let set 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onions in butter 5 to 8 minutes until tender, stirring to separate into rings.
Add sherry and cook quickly 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.

title: country spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown the spareribs in a skillet with oil. Put the ribs in a crock-pot and then add sauerkraut, brown sugar, potatoes and carrots. Add about 1/4 cup of water. Cook on low for about 8 hours.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Remove any shell from the crab meat.
Combine all the ingredients; serve on lettuce.
Shrimp may be used instead of crab meat.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Line bottom and sides of glass cake pan with vanilla wafers and then with sliced bananas, spoon pudding over all of the cookies and bananas.
Top with wafers.
Chill until pudding is set.

title: spinach quiche
directions: In a bowl, mix broccoli and cheese. Mix in another bowl the eggs and half and half. Pour over broccoli and cheese. Cook 10 minutes at 450°, then at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Mix until well blended. Add onion, pepper, pimento, lemon juice and seasoning. Mix well. Place in small mixing bowl and chill until firm. Shape into ball and roll in walnuts. Place cheese ball in center of tray surrounded by parsley. Serve with a variety of crackers on same tray. After serving, remaining cheese ball may be reshaped, rolled in nuts and refrigerated for later use.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and 1 stick of butter.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick butter.
Add eggs.
Add alternately flour and soda with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans, melted candy and butter. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: dried great northern beans
directions: Pick over beans to remove bad ones and wash.
Put meat and beans in a large pot and cover with water.
Cook slowly over medium heat for about 2 hours or until done.
Put salt in during last hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
In baking dish, crumble 1/2 box of crackers.
Cut butter in pads on top of crackers.
Pour in chicken mixture and add the remaining crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Blend 1 1/2 cup crumbs with butter.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Dissolve gelatin, 1/4 cup sugar and salt in water in top of double boiler.
Add well-beaten egg yolks; cook over hot water until thick.
Cool; add creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Congeal until consistency of egg white.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add remaining sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill.

title: sour cream tortilla casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 cup onions in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, taco mix and peppers.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Pour about 1/2 cup of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and spread to cover.
Arrange a layer of Doritos over sauce.
Top with 1/3 of sauce, onions and cheese. Repeat procedure twice, making 3 layers of Doritos.
Combine sour cream and seasoned salt.
Spread over cheese to edge of dish. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
To serve, cut into 10 or 12 squares.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until thread spins or 250 degrees on candy thermometer.
Then add peanuts and stir continuously after peanuts are added.
Cook until temperature reaches 300. Take from heat, add butter, and soda.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: lite pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and allow to cool completely.
Combine all ingredients, toss and chill.

title: steak diane
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, mix onion, garlic, salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, margarine and parsley; heat until thoroughly warm.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet; salt and pepper tenderloin slices and cook over medium high heat to medium doneness.
Place on warm platter and serve with sauce poured on top.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Pour orange juice into a mixing bowl.
Add pineapple and juice and oranges (drained).
Stir in the other fruits.
Stir in the ginger ale.
Pour mixture into 5 ounce paper cups.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.
Serve partially thawed and enjoy!

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom.
Arrange banana slices on crust.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef.
Add onion; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Stir in noodles, cooked and drained.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 30 minutes until hot.

title: apple yam bake
directions: Boil potatoes about 15 minutes or until almost tender.
Peel and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Use 2 quart casserole.
Gently toss apples and potatoes together.
Stir apple juice and cornstarch, add sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over potatoes and apples and dot with margarine.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and stir in nuts.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place
all
ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice potatoes and onion in small pieces.
Place in saucepan with salt, pepper, ham and water to cook until potatoes are tender.
Mix corn meal with water so that mixture is thick.
Add to cooking ingredients; cook until desired consistency.
Add clams; cook approximately 6 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, debone.
Mix the 2 soups together.
Add the sour cream to the soups.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add melted butter to mixture.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Melt 2 sticks margarine and 1 teaspoon of vanilla flavoring.
Pour over mixture.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin wax over boiling water in double boiler. Dip balls into mixture, one piece at a time, holding each with a toothpick.
Reduce heat to simmer; let cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half of batter into floured and greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt caramel and margarine and add milk.
Mix and pour over cake while hot.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter over this.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes, then bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix together macaroni, tuna, soup, olives, milk and cheese.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: smoked beans(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon; drain.
Add all other ingredients into a slow cooker.
Stir well to mix.
Cook for 5 to 6 hours on low.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Set aside and let cool.
Prepare stuffing as directed on boxes.
When chicken is cooked, pick apart and shred.
Throw skin away.
Mix chicken with soup.
In casserole dish put half of the stuffing down, then put chicken mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. You may top with shredded cheese.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put eggs in large
jar.
Mix
all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over eggs.
Let stand for 2 days.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread raisins and nuts in bottom of pan.
Cut bread in walnut-size pieces and place in single layer.
Heat remaining ingredients in pan and pour over top. Refrigerate uncovered overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn out immediately.
Serves lots.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten thick and lemon colored (5 minutes).
Combine sifted flour and baking powder and add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavoring.
Spoon mixture into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Then add glaze.

title: rosemary's candy
directions: Cook sugar, butter, syrup and milk together over low heat for 30 minutes.
Stir the mixture.
Add nuts or coconut and cook on high until a few drops of candy form a soft ball when tested (230° to 240° on candy thermometer).
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla and cool to lukewarm and beat hard until mixture loses gloss and starts to hold shape.
Pour into large buttered pan or spoon into little mounds on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
To this add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Put into containers such as margarine tubs and freeze.
Put in the punch bowl.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up. We prefer strawberry over cherry jello.

title: orange balls(no bake)
directions: Mix well.
Form in 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Keep in a cool place.

title: beefy burritos
directions: Cook beef and onion until tender.
Add 1/2 cup cheese. Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Set aside.
Warm tortillas in foil in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Top each tortilla with 2 teaspoons meat mixture.
Roll up and put in casserole dish.
Pour soups and sauce over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve candies in hot water.
Pour over Jell-O, stirring to dissolve.
Add applesauce and chill until partially set.
Fold in celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: peach trifle
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in saucepan; bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool. Fold in half whipped topping.
Sprinkle sugar over peaches; toss and set aside.
Place 1/2 of cake in bottom of 16-cup trifle bowl and drizzle with half of orange juice.
Arrange half of peaches over cake and top with half of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers. Spread remaining whipped topping on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill at least 2 hours.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
flour and cornmeal.
Add butter, lemon juice, lemon
rind
and
milk;
mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after
each	addition.
Pour into shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 muffin cups.
Mix thoroughly shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Alternate with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in airtight container.
To use, put 2 heaping teaspoons in a cup.
Add hot water and stir.
Enjoy with or without marshmallows.

title: chafing dish crab mornay
directions: Thaw frozen crabmeat.
Drain.
Remove any remaining shell cartilage.
Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook onion and parsley in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour.
Add cream slowly and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Add cheese, wine and seasonings.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add crabmeat and mix carefully.
Serve in a chafing dish with assorted crackers.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package.
Cool.
Add bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Pour half of this mixture into a greased pan or mold.
Chill until jelled.
Spread sour cream on top, then pour remaining jello over all.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Pecans may be added, if desired.

title: colorful carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice lengthwise into slim strips, about 4-inches long.
Boil until tender, but still crisp (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain.
Cut away seeds and white membrane from inside green pepper and cut it into slim strips.
Peel and thinly slice onion and separate into rings.
Lay all this in an oblong dish (8 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Stir well and while hot, pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate when cool.

title: crock-pot chicken or chuck roast
directions: Spray inside of pot with cooking spray oil.
Put carrots, celery, potatoes, onion and salt in bottom of pot.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Pour chicken soup over top; makes gravy.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add brown sugar, ketchup, vinegar, molasses, mustard and salt.
Add all beans.
Cook in 325° oven for 2 to 3 hours or cooks great in crock-pot.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer until batter is smooth. Pour batter into a greased and floured bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in oil until smooth.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Add nuts and apples; mix well.
Turn into a greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool cake in pan or on a wire rack and spread smoothly with lemon cheese icing.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions until done.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients and simmer about one hour.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, chestnuts and onions. Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Trim off soil leaves and remove core.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes or until leaves are limp.
Separate leaves, carefully reserving 5 of the largest leaves for the rolls. Combine meat thoroughly with onion, egg, milk and salt.
Place 1/3 of the mixture on each leaf and fold up in envelope fashion. Fasten with toothpick.
Lay flap side down in Dutch oven or saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup water, cover rolls with the rest of the cabbage leaves.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve with tomato sauce.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Tear cabbage into small pieces. Mix ingredients together; chill.

title: martha crane's w.g.n. 1930's
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar
together; let stand 3 hours. Boil fast for 8 minutes.
Then add 4 tablespoons lemon juice. Boil 2 minutes more.
Cool and can when cold.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese in large bowl until smooth; gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on graham crust.
Mix 1 cup milk and pudding until thick.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours and garnish with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Put softened ice cream in a large bowl. Add all boxes of instant pudding. Add 3 cups milk.
Mix with mixer. Crush 1/2 box Ritz crackers and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save small amount to cover top of mixture.
Pour in mixture and cover top of mixture. Refrigerate until set up.

title: baked salmon
directions: Mix like meat loaf and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with lemon.

title: lemon bread
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition. Stir in rind.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven or until toothpick test comes out clean.

title: shasta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Poke holes in cake with finger or wooden spoon handle when cool.
In separate bowl, put 1 can of strawberry pop.
Add enough water to the pop to make 2 cups liquid.
Boil. Add strawberry jello to liquid.
Pour into holes and refrigerate until cool.
Mix vanilla instant pudding with a little less milk than it calls for.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Ice cake.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix together remaining dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk mixture.
Stir just until mixed.
Fill greased muffin pans (or use paper muffin cups) about 2/3 full.
Bake for 18 minutes at 400°.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, mustard and bread cubes; mix.
Add cheese and sausage.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fancy chicken breasts
directions: Cook chicken breasts in large pan with some water until tender.
(The flavor of the chicken is improved if an onion, a carrot and a stalk of celery are cooked with the chicken.
Also you can season with salt and pepper to taste.)

title: fruit tea smoothie
directions: In teapot, pour boiling water over tea bags. Cover and brew 5 minutes. Remove tea bags. Stir in sugar and lemon juice. Chill. For every four servings, in 5 cup blender, combine 3/4 cup tea mixture, 1 1/2 cups strawberries, 1/3 cantaloupe and 2 1/2 cups crushed ice. Process at high speed until well blended. Garnish with fresh fruit or mint leaves.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Mix together sour cream and instant pudding.
Drain pineapple and fold into sour cream and pudding mixture.
Pour into crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with slivered almonds or nuts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cocktail sauce together until smooth, then fold in shrimp.

title: nordstrom's nordy bars
directions: In medium sauce pan, melt butter over medium heat; add butterscotch chips and brown sugar stirring until melted. Remove from heat and stir in eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt mixing thoroughly. Stir in vanilla, set-aside until cool. When cool, stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow and pecans. Spread into greased 9x12 inch pan. Bake 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and grapes.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Combine all ingredients and let sit overnight.

title: hearty corn chowder
directions: Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to boiling water.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes until cooked.
Do not drain.

title: hot ham 'n cheese
directions: Melt margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion flakes and poppy seed together.
Stir well; bring to a boil.
Split bread and spread about 1 teaspoon sauce on each roll.
Layer ham and cheese on rolls, then pour remaining sauce over the top of the rolls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Add vanilla to butter.
Add sugar (5 tablespoons).
Add water, flour and nuts.
Shape into balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.
Roll in remaining sugar.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Put whipping cream, dry pudding and nutmeg in bowl; whip until peaks form. Spoon into baked pie shell; top with can of pie filling. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chicken with rice and mushroom sauce
directions: Butter medium pan or casserole dish. Pour rice into dish. Pour broth over rice.
Place chicken next.
Spread soup (undiluted) over chicken.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: rueben casserole
directions: Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer: Rye bread, corned beef, sauerkraut, Thousand Island dressing, Swiss cheese and rye bread.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: deep fried okra
directions: Wash okra, drain, cut off tips and cut crosswise. Combine flour, meal, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in shallow dish.
Set aside flour mixture.

title: lavender tea
directions: Steep in boiling water.
Sweeten with honey to taste. Europeans drink Lavender Tea to soothe their nerves.
This serves 2.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in pan.
Let come to boil on stove, then add egg yolks, flour and 1 cup milk.
Cook until thick.
Put in pie shell.
Top with meringue made from egg whites.

title: econo potato bake
directions: This is a wonderful dish, especially if you don't have much time or money.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together until thoroughly blended. Chill and serve with fruit, i.e. sliced apples, grapes, bananas, fresh pineapple, strawberries, etc.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Subway....they are the best!! No clean up!!

title: orange salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Stir in jello and mix well.
Cool. Add buttermilk and then Cool Whip.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and quickly add oats, peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla. Blend and drop by a teaspoon on wax paper. Cookies will set quickly.

title: twiced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes.
Bake them until they are done.
Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the potatoes, leaving a shell.
Rice the potatoes.
Beat in cream cheese and enough sour cream to lighten the mixture.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of minced onion if desired.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refill the potato shells.
Garnish with paprika and/or chervil.
Serves 8.

title: christmas drops
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; dredge in 1/2 cup flour, stirring well.
Set aside.
Beat butter in a large mixing bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add brown sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add buttermilk.
Combine remaining 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets immediately and cool on wire racks.
Store at room temperature in airtight container or freeze.
Yields 12 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Boil sugar and water for about 10 minutes.
Allow to cool, then add the fruit pulp and lemon juice.
Blend well and freeze in ice cream cooler.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Do not salt chicken before cooking.

title: herman coffee cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together (plus raisins, if using them).
Do not use electric mixer.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: choco-caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside. Combine cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup milk. Press half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes.
Spread nuts and chocolate chips over baked dough. Spread melted caramel mixture on chips and nuts. Crumble rest of cake mix over top. Bake 20 minutes. Cool well and cut into bars when firm.

title: egg noodle stroganoff
directions: Wonderful, rich fish dish enjoyed by many.
Use fresh spinach for perfect bed.
Serve with French bread, and carrot/pea/scallion vegetables.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and then sugar.
Beat well.
Add beaten eggs, flour, and dash of salt.
Mix well and stir in nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: chocolate mini-mousse
directions: Combine 1/3 cup skim milk and gelatin in blender container and wait one minute before adding water.
Blend until gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining milk, sugar, cocoa and vanilla; blend. Add ice milk and blend until smooth and creamy.
Spoon into dessert cups.
Chill until set.
Contains 70 calories per 4 ounce serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Form softened cream cheese into ball.
Pour cocktail sauce over cheese ball.
Drain shrimp well and put over sauce.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a greased 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread can of fruit on top and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Top with vanilla ice cream and serve warm.

title: caramel-pecan cheese pie
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/3 cup water. Let stand for 1 minute. Bring to a boil; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved. Cool slightly. In a blender or food processor, combine lemon juice, cream cheese and gelatin mixture; cover and process until smooth. Transfer to a large bowl; fold in whipped topping. Stir in 3 tablespoons of the pecans. Pour mixture into crust; top with remaining nuts. Drizzle with caramel topping. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours, until set.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onion in layers in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over.
Bake, covered, at 375° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shelia's favorite pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle to 350°.
Whisk all dry ingredients together before whisking in liquids.
Whisk in egg, milk and melted butter. Batter should be lumpy.
Do not beat until smooth.
Use 1/2 cup measuring cup to pour batter onto griddle.
Turn once when pancake surface appears bubbly.

title: puppy chow
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter and melt over low heat on a range or in the microwave.
Pour this mixture over the cereal and stir to coat.
Place powdered sugar in a brown bag. Pour cereal mixture into the bag and shake to coat pieces.
Store in an airtight container.

title: french buttercream cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients on low speed of mixer about 1 minute.
Blend well.
Chill dough about 15 to 20 minutes before shaping into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets. Flatten with fork and bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
This is a soft light cookie.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: anna's favorite tortellini
directions: Cook rainbow tortellini according to directions on package. Drain, cool and cut in half to make bite sized.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
No utensils required! Just ask Anna!!

title: two ton dessert
directions: Mix like pastry and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Let cool whip get to room temperature. Melt candy bars and mix with cool whip. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Don't over season; sauce will pick up more of the seasoning as it sits in the refrigerator.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix by hand only.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain well (reserve juice). Saute onion; add flour and other ingredients. Add cheese and mix. Pour over spinach. Serve hot.

title: mexican avocado dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados and mix with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Spoon lightly into measuring cup and level without shaking or packing down.
Combine flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
With a pastry blender or two knives, cut in shortening until uniform.
Mixture should be fairly coarse. Sprinkle with water, a tablespoon at a time.
Toss with a fork. Work dough into a firm ball with your hands.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff and set aside.
Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time and cream well.
Slowly add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in flavoring, coconut, pecans and cherries.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. May use Bundt pan or 9 x 13 cake pan.
For icing, mix cream cheese and butter well.
Add flavoring.
Stir in sugar a little at a time until well blended.
Add nuts.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dough (1 to 1 1/2-inch balls) about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheets before moving to wire racks to cool thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: oatmeal coconut
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 15 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil in bowl and beat. Sift flour, baking soda and spices. Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Make sure zucchini is well blended. Finally, fold in the sour cream. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick pierced into the center of the bread comes out clean.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix peanut butter, sugar and butter

with electric mixer until well blended and smooth. Roll mixture into 1 inch balls. Place on waxed paper lined baking sheet. Chill at least 20 minutes. Carefully melt chocolate chips in double boiler. Using a skewer, dip balls into chocolate to cover. Set on wax paper until hardened. Store in fridge.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Beat eggs real well.
Add sugar and fruit juice. Cook over medium heat until thick. (Will not be very thick.)
Cool before pouring over fruit.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Drain and flake salmon. Reserve liquid.
Saute celery, onion and garlic until translucent. Add potatoes, carrots, broth and seasoning.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: blt pizza
directions: Spread pizza crust with mayo, then layer tomatoes, cheese and bacon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with lettuce and serve.

title: wild rice and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Pour rice into colander and drain well.
Melt butter; add flour and stir until a thick paste.
Add milk slowly.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted and sauce is smooth.
Butter 1 1/2-quart (8 x 8-inch) casserole. Layer rice, mushrooms and cream cheese sauce.
Repeat until dish is filled.
Save enough sauce to put generous amount of sauce on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until mixture is hot.

title: del matto's creamy italian
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: bloody mary
directions: Pour vodka into highball glass; add Worcestershire sauce, pepper, celery salt and Tabasco.
Fill glass with ice and fill with mix.
Squeeze a lime wedge and add to drink.
Mix well.
May add a stalk of celery with leaves on it.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve syrup.
Add
enough
water
to make 1/2 cup.
Dissolve gelatin and
sugar in 1 cup hot water. Add syrup and lemon juice.
Chill
until
partially set.
Stir in fruits, celery and nuts.
Chill in mold until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spray pan with Pam (disposable 12 1/4 x 8 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch aluminum pan works great).
Take 1 can of rolls and spread on bottom of pan (do not separate rolls).
Soften cream cheese and add sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spread mixture over rolls in pan.
Spread second can of rolls on top of mixture.
Beat egg white until "frothy"; brush on top of top layer of rolls.
You don't need to use all the egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fresh french-fried mushrooms
directions: Trim fresh mushrooms.
Wash and wipe with damp paper towel. Mix egg and milk.
Dip fresh, prepared mushrooms into mixture, then into flour or cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot, deep fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Salt to taste.
Serve hot.

title: eggplant and hoisin sauce
directions: Mix pork with cornstarch, soy and wine and set aside.
Salt cut up eggplant and set aside to drain.
Stir-fry pork in peanut oil until tender. Set aside. Stir-fry eggplant until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add pork and heat throughout.
Top with parsley and serve.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Empty small can of crushed pineapple into saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add lime Jell-O and boil 2 minutes more.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese, chopped nuts, unflavored gelatin in cold water, dissolved over hot water.
Add ginger ale to gelatin mixture and combine with pineapple mixture.
Blend in 1/2 pint whipped whipping cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients real good and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: godfather's oysters
directions: Cut rolls in half.
Put in 1 thin slice of butter.
Put on 1 oyster.
Sprinkle with Old Bay to taste.
Bake at 325° until oyster edges curl.

title: chocolate macaroon cookies
directions: Mix all together.
With a teaspoon, drop onto a greased cookie sheet and bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: poached eggs provencale
directions: Place undrained tomatoes in 10-inch frying pan and cut them into wedges or chunks with a spoon.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except eggs.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Carefully break eggs into simmering vegetable mixture.
Cover and cook eggs to desired doneness, 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon eggs and vegetable mixture into serving dishes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roast pork loin deluxe
directions: Have meat at room temperature.
Rub meat all over with lemon juice and then salt.
Combine spices and rub well into meat. Place bay leaf, parsley, celery, onion and garlic and consomme around meat.
Cover.
Roast at 350°.
Baste every 30 minutes. Roast approximately 35 minutes per pound until meat is tender and brown.

title: southwestern rice pilaf
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper, carrot and celery and saute until vegetables begin to soften, about 5 minutes.
Add broth and bring to simmer.
Cover skillet; reduce heat to low and simmer until rice is tender and broth is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Mix in tomato and jalapeno.
Season pilaf with salt and pepper to taste and serve.

title: six minute broccoli
directions: *To toast sesame seed, heat dry skillet.
Add seed.
Stir until light brown, 2 to 3 minutes or roast 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let sit for 6 hours before serving.
Drain off most of the liquid.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with onions.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Reduce heat and blend in cream cheese.
Add to broccoli and onions in a casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: lauree's lobster in garlic sauce
directions: In deep baking dish, cut potatoes.
Slice onion in rings and pepper into strips.
Chop garlic.
Season to your taste.
Season lobster in shell.
Place lobsters over vegetable mixture in pan. Squeeze Parkay over lobsters and vegetables.
Every 10 minutes squeeze Parkay over lobsters.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting often.
Serve garlic sauce, potatoes and onion over hot rice with lobster.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; add 3 heaping teaspoons of flour and stir until dissolved.
Add 3 cups broth and stir until bubbly. Slowly add milk.
Place chicken, veggies and chestnuts in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over this.
Take biscuits and separate them, putting them on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits turn brown.

title: lemony cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.

title: old fashioned bread pudding(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an 8-inch pan, spread bread and raisins.
Whisk 2 cups
of milk, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and salt in bowl.
Pour over bread.
Let stand 15 minutes, turning bread once.

title: melt in your mouth cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and vegetable oil until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift soda, flour, cream of tartar and salt together and then add to mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Roll into small balls.
Press flat with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place jello in a large mixing bowl; add 2 cups boiling water. Stir to dissolve jello.
Add cranberry sauce so heat will melt the sauce.
Stir or whisk lightly.
Add cup of cold water.
Chop apples and celery; stir into salad.
Pour into rectangular container and refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve, or spoon out for buffet service.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat well. Add mashed bananas and vanilla. Add flour to which salt and soda have been added. Add walnuts. Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour. Bake longer if not done, approximately 1 1/4 hours.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish. Spread cheese over mixture.
Mix crushed crackers with melted oleo.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: myrt's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in buttered casserole.
Cover top with cubed bread sauteed in butter and sprinkle with garlic salt (sparingly).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: 2 step chicken broccoli divan
directions: In shallow casserole, arrange broccoli.
Top with chicken. Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine oleo and bread crumbs; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add egg. Stir in vinegar and pineapple juice. Heat to soft boil. Remove from heat when thickened and cool. Combine in bowl: apples, crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and peanuts. Mix with cooled sauce and refrigerate.

title: orange baskets(ornaments for birds)
directions: Note:
Need 12 feet (1/2-inch wide) ribbon.

title: novel baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, saute ham and onion in butter until onion is tender (not brown).
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine pork and beans, ketchup, brown sugar and mustard. Stir in ham mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken with peanut sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from chicken and place in lightly oiled baking dish.
Heat oil and saute onion and garlic. Spread onion, garlic and chopped apple over the chicken. Gradually add the chicken broth to the peanut sauce, beating with a fork until smooth.
Pour over the chicken pieces.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake until tender. Yield:
4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and put in baking dish. Top with the crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour the melted margarine over the crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Very good!

title: yellow squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and pour into a baking dish (greased).
Cover with melted butter and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Combine brown sugar and cream cheese until smooth and creamy. Slice fresh fruit, dipping into juice to keep from turning brown.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix together and shape into a loaf.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with 8 ounces tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese snow flakes(by sherry sons - won 1st place in 4-h)
directions: Preheat oven at 375°. Cut butter and cheese into sifted flour and baking powder as pie crust. Add cold water and mix well. Fill cookie press plate No. 13. Press snow flakes onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown. Remove to cooling rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Crush crackers.
Melt butter and cut up cheese to melt.
Mix butter and crackers.
Cut cooked broccoli into small pieces.
Put a layer of broccoli on bottom of casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 of cracker crumbs on top of broccoli.
Place sliced cheese on top and repeat layers.
Melt the reserved 2 tablespoons butter and pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp, with an electric beater. Fold shrimp in by hand.
Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/2 and shake in bag with sugar mixture.
Put in Bundt pan.
Add walnuts between layers.

title: pistachio whip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well until creamy and refrigerate.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar (10x).
Add water and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add flour; fold in pecans.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and flatten with fingers.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: easy taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and onions; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix, beans and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles.
Place in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust.
Brush dough with oil; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon hot meat mixture over crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Cut into squares.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs, diluting soup according to directions on can.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until nice and brown.
Layer with sliced eggs and serve.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Boil spareribs 1 1/2 hours. Add cabbage, carrots, onion and potatoes. Salt to taste. Boil for 20 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound cutlets thin.
Beat together 1 egg and 2 egg whites. dip cutlets in egtg mixture, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown in olive oil nad drain on paper towels.
In square baking pan spread some sauce on bottom, then lay chicken on bottom, pour some sauce over chicken, then sprinkle grated parmesan cheese over chicken.
Cover with shredded mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°F.
Serve with angel hair pasta or wide noodles.

title: pecan creams
directions: Crumble 1/2 cup butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 cup sifted flour together and press into bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs and add 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Add pecans and coconut. Pour on top of baked mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain.
Stir butter (or margarine) into hot spaghetti.
Stir in eggs and Parmesan. Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over "crust".
In a skillet cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until vegetables and meat are tender and meat is slightly browned.
Drain well.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt; heat through.
Turn meat mixture into crust.
Bake uncovered in350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella atop and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Select firm, ripened peaches.
Peel peaches.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Can use pickling spices, but remove peppers. Boil 10 minutes.
Add a few peaches at a time in boiling sugar and cook until just tender.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Fill with boiling syrup and seal.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine together hamburger, eggs, salt and pepper. Make into 1 inch balls. Fry meatballs until brown. Heat jelly and ketchup in large saucepan on medium heat until jelly and ketchup are melted. Put meatballs in sauce; cook on medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese sandwich cookies
directions: Slice one package dough thin and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat to form crust.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Slice second package of cookie dough thin and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Fill in spaces as best you can.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: broccoli stuffing bake
directions: Mix thawed broccoli with condensed soup, contents of cornbread dressing package, salt and pepper in a greased 2-quart casserole. Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Five minutes before it is done, sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour 2 cups into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, in a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and oleo with milk. Stir until smooth.
Spread over cake, spread remaining batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until cake springs back.
Cool; garnish as desired.

title: rice
directions: Saute onion, carrot and garlic in oil.
Add rice and salt. Stir until it is coated with oil.
Bring to a boil and cover. Cook over a low heat for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple into casserole dish; sprinkle flour mixture over it.
Put cheese over this, then crackers.
Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Cook at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hoppin' john(black-eyed peas and rice)
directions: Place ham hocks in a large saucepan.
Add water to cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add bay leaf, onions, celery and seasonings. Sort out and discard any discolored or damaged peas.
Rinse remainder well and add to the pot.
If necessary, adjust water level so that the peas are well covered.
Simmer slowly until tender and liquid level is low for about 2 hours.
Cook rice separately until fluffy.
Mix peas into rice.
Add more seasoning, if needed, and cook over low heat until all liquid is absorbed.

title: five ingredient punch
directions: Peel (remember to save the peels, see Peel recipes), section, peel sections.
Pack in rigid containers, cover with medium syrup, 2 cups sugar dissolved in 1 cup water.
Seal and freeze.
These will store 6 to 10 months.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs and add to squash; add margarine and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on hot griddle and brown.

title: cheese cake(yields 10 servings)
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Put first three ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix for 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Scrape down the mixing bowl.
Add light cream and mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and mix again.

title: banana-oatmeal drops
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Saute mushrooms in garlic butter.
Saute green onions.
Fry eggs and combine all of these with rice.
Crunch up a small bag of almonds and add to mixture. Sprinkle with garlic and let everything sit before serving.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt package of almond bark and chocolate chips.
Add peanuts and drop onto waxed paper to harden.

title: nettie brinkley's pound cake
directions: Cream
butter, oil and sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour and milk, alternating.	Add flavoring last.
Grease and flour pan. Place
in
cold oven.
Set oven to 300°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Don't open door during baking.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and oleo until melted.
Add flour; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch; spread mixture on the bottom and up the sides a little.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Pastry will puff up like a cream puff.
Let cool.

title: graham cracker brittle cookie
directions: On a 10 x 13-inch pan, lay out graham sections.
Sprinkle with slicked natural almonds.
Try to leave no nuts over the cracks. (Fit crackers tight together).
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes the butter, margarine and sugar.
Drizzle over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from pan onto foil.
Separate.
When cool, pop off the foil.
Store in airtight tin.

title: jello popcorn treat
directions: Heat and stir together Karo syrup and butter.
Gradually add package of Jell-O.
Spread popcorn over cookie sheet which is covered with aluminum foil.
Pour Jell-O substance over popcorn evenly.
Bake in oven at 325° on cookie sheet for 10 minutes. Take out of oven and put in bowl.
Enjoy!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour cheese mixture over crust carefully.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Cool 5 minutes.
Mix the sour cream, vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Pour over cheese cake and put in oven for 5 minutes at 275°.
Cool in refrigerator or freezer.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, gelatin and sugar and stir in boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Let cool for a while. Stir in melted ice cream. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Freeze until firm.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water. Let stand 20 minutes. Cream sugars and shortening. Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients and stir in sugar mixture. Add oatmeal mixture and raisins. Mix thoroughly. Bake in a 9 X 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Test doneness by touching gently.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine in a large pan, sugar, cocoa, margarine, salt and milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Mix together thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: eatable valentine cards
directions: Using table knife, cover each graham cracker with frosting. Decorate, write friends name or initials, or write a greeting by pressing candies firmly into icing.

title: sheath cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Heat butter, cocoa, water and shortening to boil; pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 11 x 15 inch pan and bake for
20 minutes at 400°.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Grease and flour four 16 ounce size tin cans.
Pour boiling water over raisins and oil and let cool.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir everything into the water and raisins.
Fill cans 2/3 full and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Excellent served with cream cheese.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Put between wafers, using three for each ball.
(Wafers are stacked with filling between them.) Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
A few hours before serving, coat with whip cream and coconut.
Makes 20.

title: hot herb bread - italian style
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Blend butter, parsley flakes, oregano, dill weed and garlic.
Put bread slices together again with butter mixture in between.
Shape Reynolds Wrap around loaf boat-fashion, twisting ends and leaving top open. Sprinkle top liberally with cheese and parsley flakes.
Heat in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add beaten egg to milk.
Dissolve yeast and warm water.
Add to egg mixture.
Cut shortening into flour.
Mix flour and egg mixture.
Knead and roll dough to about 1-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter.
Brush tops with butter or margarine.
Place on greased cookie sheet and cover with towel.
Let rise 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in preheated oven.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Melt butter. Pour over pecans. Add coconut, milk, sugar and vanilla. Mix well. Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate. Place on waxed paper until firm.

title: sweet pickled watermelon rind
directions: Pare rind from watermelon.
Cover with water and simmer until tender, about 1/2 hour.
Drain.
Make syrup by bringing to a boil the sugar, vinegar and oils.
Pour over rind.
Let stand overnight.

title: artichoke bake appetizer
directions: Drain and chop artichokes and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients in ovenproof shallow dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top should be light brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: orange filling for angel food cake
directions: Boil over medium heat the first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly. Pour over the beaten eggs and return to boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add the butter and lemon juice. Let cool. Slice an angel food cake into 3 layers. Add the Cool Whip to the orange filling and spread between layers. Frost cake with Cool Whip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine ingredients in shallow glass baking dish.
Cover. Cook in microwave oven for 7 to 9 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, stirring occasionally.
Serve on a bun.
Total cooking time: about 8 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 9-inch Keebler graham cracker or regular pie crust.
Refrigerate for several hours, until filling is set.

title: sausage strata
directions: Cook bulk sausage over medium heat until done.
Pour out on paper towel and blot to remove grease.
Tear 6 slices white bread (stale is fine) into cubes and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the bread with the cooked sausage. Sprinkle the sausage with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Pour this over sausage mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jennifer's chicken toes(pollo alla cacciatore)
directions: Heat oil with garlic in a large fry pan.
When garlic is golden, discard it.
Put in chicken, rosemary and salt; brown thoroughly on both sides of chicken.
When chicken is golden brown, add the wine vinegar and quickly cover until the sizzling stops. Now add wine and cook on high heat until vapors evaporate.
Reduce the heat and simmer 15 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon water to pan.
Scrape pan; pour over chicken.

title: meatball stew
directions: Crush corn flakes.
Stir in egg, 1/4 cup beef broth, salt and pepper.
Add ground chuck; shape into balls.
Brown.
Add remaining ingredients; cook 30 minutes.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.

Add the tomato sauce, water, tomato paste, salt and oregano; mix well. Spread 1/4 of the meat sauce in an ungreased 5-quart slow cooker. Arrange 1/3 of the noodles over the sauce. Combine the cheeses; spoon 1/3 of the mixture over the noodles. Repeat layers twice. Top with remaining meat sauce. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until noodles are tender.

title: david's chili
directions: Fry seasoned hamburger and onions.
Drain fat.
Add 1 package chili seasoning mix.
Stir in well.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually and beat until smooth.
Then add cool, melted margarine and the anise.
Fold in sifted flour and baking powder.
Drop from teaspoon into the center of hot pizzelle iron.
Preheat iron before mixing up the batter.

title: easy fudgemallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Makes 2 dozen squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and chill.
Fold in the cranberry sauce.
Add walnuts, if desired.

title: wined and chived chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer on wax paper.
Gently squeeze lemon half and rub juice completely over chicken.
Mix sugar and pepper and sprinkle on chicken.
Fold wax paper over chicken; press chicken lightly, making sure sugar-pepper mixture adheres to chicken.
In frying pan, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook chicken, turning until brown.
Remove chicken and set aside.
In same frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Saut mushrooms and garlic.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add chicken broth, wine and chives; cook, stirring until sauce thickens.
Return chicken to frying pan and simmer, uncovered, about 45 minutes, turning occasionally.
Cook chicken until fork-tender.
Stir in cream, paprika and salt; heat 2 minutes more.
Place one piece of chicken on each slice of toasted bread and spoon sauce over chicken.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add shortening and mix with fork or pastry blender until ingredients are crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough in four portions and wrap each portion with plastic or wax paper and chill at least 1/2 hour.
(May be frozen for later use.)

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown the pork chops in the oil.
Put in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Season.
Mix the rice, onion, water, salt and soup.
Pour evenly over the pork chops. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until meat and rice are done. Add more water, if necessary.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and next 5 ingredients; saute 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Remove vegetable mixture from heat; set aside and keep warm.
Combine water and Cajun seasoning in a medium saucepan, stirring well. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Combine vegetable mixture and cooked rice in a large bowl.
Add chopped parsley and toss gently to combine.
Yields 4 cups.

title: light buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring until flour is just moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Bake on hot griddle.

title: kelly's dip
directions: Cut top off bread loaf and scoop out center, leaving shell. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon into bread shell. Replace top.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dip for veggies or bread
directions: Mix everything together well, chill and serve.

title: great salad
directions: This can be made ahead and mixed together the day before you are going to use it.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind together.
Let stand overnight first 3 ingredients. Then rinse and drain.
Mix together and add chopped peppers and seasonings.
Cook all ingredients for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Follow directions on the box of cake mix for a 9 x 13-inch cake and bake. While cake is baking, combine together the caramel and butterscotch toppings and the sweetened condensed milk. Heat together on top of the stove, but do not boil.

title: granola
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 3. Heat honey and oil and add vanilla.
Mix into other ingredients.
Spread in large, shallow, greased pan and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 200°, stirring every 30 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes and salt in water; reserve water.
In skillet, saute onion in oil until soft.
In blender, blend potatoes, potato water, onion, milk and parsley until smooth.
Only fill blender halfway to avoid sticking.
Return mixture to stove and, stirring continuously, add margarine, pepper, garlic powder and grated cheese.

title: chow mein noodle clusters
directions: Melt chips in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles, nuts and vanilla so they are evenly coated.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill and refrigerate.

title: lazy pierogis
directions: Rinse kraut in cold water and cook it early or the night before.
When cool, squeeze out as much water as possible.
Fry kraut in butter with mushrooms.
In another frypan, fry bacon. Take bacon out; put onions in and saute.
Add all ingredients with cooked noodles and bake in casserole dish 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prick 1 pie shell with fork and bake about 3 minutes.

Break chicken into bite size pieces; put in bottom of pie crust. Melt oleo in saucepan; add flour and stir until smooth. Add broth and milk, cooking until it thickens. Add drained vegetables and black pepper. Pour over chicken and top with other pie crust. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs for 10 minutes.
Add flour and milk; beat well.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: baked milk fish
directions: Prepare an 8 x 8 baking dish with cooking spray. Rinse cod fillets and pat dry. Place fish in a single layer in the baking dish. Mix together the milk, onion, lemon pepper and parsley (add salt, if using). Pour over the cod fillets. Drizzle lemon juice over top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until fish is firm and can be flaked with a fork.

title: easy cheesecake dessert
directions: Place liners in cupcake pan.
Put one vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner.
Mix together in a blender the cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Place this mixture on top of each vanilla wafer.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
When cool completely, add cherry pie filling on top and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together and drain fat.
Add soups and sauces.
Cook and simmer until hot and bubbly.
Tear corn tortillas apart and line casserole dish.
Put layers of sauce and then layers of cheese and more tortillas.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: simply elegant shrimp
directions: Heat butter and oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute until transparent.
Stir in broth, salad dressing, herbs, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; add shrimp and cook until pink. Stir in fresh parsley.
Serve with rice or fettucine.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth. Spread on a 12-inch round platter.
Cover with cocktail sauce. Sprinkle with cheese, shrimp, onions and tomato.
Cover and chill. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops over med high heat. Season with salt & pepper. Combine potatoes, carrots, onions, salt, marjoram, and pepper. Mix lightly.
Place in 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Pour mushroom soup over potato mixture.
Top with chops. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 - 1 3/4 hours until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp, spinach and cheese souffle
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Fold in spinach and shrimp.
Beat egg yolks 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in shrimp mixture.
Wash beaters and in large mixer bowl beat egg whites to stiff peaks. Gradually fold egg whites into shrimp mixture.
Turn mixture into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix together cake mix,egg, and margarine; add nuts. Put into a greased 9 inch cake pan. In a sauce pan melt 8 oz.
