of cream cheese. Add 2 well beated eggs and 1 box of powdered sugar.Stir until well mixed on low heat. Cover the cake mix with this mixture and bake at 350° until browned.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Melt the butter in a baking pan at 250°.
Remove pan from the oven and increase the heat to 350°.
In a small bowl combine bread crumbs, parsley, cheese, salt and garlic powder.
Lay chicken pieces in pan, and turn over to coat with melted butter.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange in single layer in pan.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour, basting twice.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut all fat off the meat.
Slice meat with the grain in strips 1/8 - 1/4 thick, 6 inches long and 1/2 to 1-inch wide.
Season liberally with soy sauce and other seasonings.
If using venison, allow to marinate several hours or overnight.
Lay strips on dehydrator racks, not overcrowding.
Rotate racks, top to bottom, every four to six hours to allow for even drying.
Total drying time will depend on quantity; at least 10-12 hours.
Jerky should be dry and chewy.
An oven may be used in place of the dehydrator. Heat oven to 150°.
Lay strips across cooling racks placed on cookie sheets.
Place cookie sheets in oven.
If necessary, leave the oven door ajar to keep the temperature at 150°.
Rotate sheets every 4-6 hours.
If the temperature goes above 150°, the meat will be too crisp.

title: chewy fudge brownies
directions: Melt together chocolate and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Drain fat.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Combine spaghetti and all other ingredients except 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and sliced Mozzarella.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato souffle
directions: Beat together the mashed potatoes and egg yolks.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley and minced ham.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; fold into potato mixture.
Place in greased open casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve immediately.

title: hornets nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add cake mix. Stir until smooth.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Sprinkle with chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Freezes well.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Combine pancake mix, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon; add remaining ingredients, mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jerky
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and freeze.
Then slice while still partly frozen into thin strips.
Lay on racks; brush with remaining ingredients.
Bake or dehydrate on low heat until done, 4 to 6 hours.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine onion and green pepper in 1 quart microwavable casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until heated through.

title: cholesterol free pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add Egg Beaters and egg white.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 25 minutes.
It's good. This is a prize winning cake in the Men's Bake-Off at the church.

title: peach melba ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and gelatin in saucepan.
Add eggs and milk. Cook, stirring until mixture thickens slightly.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in cream, vanilla, and salt.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions until ice cream is nearly firm.
Add fruits.
Continue freezing until firm. Let ripen.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant.
Salt and pepper; cut into squares.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes.
Drain.
Mix cheese, crackers, eggs and milk; stir thoroughly.
Bake in a greased casserole pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves about 5 to 6.

title: preacher potatoes
directions: Fry bacon to a crisp brown and remove from pan.
Place cubed potatoes, chopped onions and green peppers in bacon grease and cook to a golden brown, stirring to keep from sticking and until pepper is tender.
Add bacon (bacon should be diced or broken into small pieces).
Salt and pepper to own taste.

title: tangy beef stew
directions: Saute onion and pepper in shortening in a large skillet.
Add ground beef and brown well. Add tomato juice, rice, chili powder and seasonings.
Stir well. Pour into casserole; cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick and pour into baked pie shell.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with additional grated cheese.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Heat butter in large skillet or Dutch oven; add chicken pieces and brown on both sides.
Add garlic, mushrooms and green pepper; cook a few minutes longer.
Add chicken broth; reduce heat to simmer and add shredded orange peel of 1 orange.
Season with salt.
Cover; cook gently for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Blend flour with a small amount of water; stir into skillet.
Heat and stir until boiling.
Section oranges; add with tomatoes and stir until heated through.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat to serving temperature. Makes 6 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan, filling side up.
Slice the bananas. Add the pudding mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in beans, almonds and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir and top with leftover onions.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more!

title: maple bacon dressing for garden salad
directions: Process all of the ingredients together in a food processor until well blended.
Pour dressing into container with an airtight lid and refrigerate until serving.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat butterscotch chips, corn syrup, margarine or butter and vanilla in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until butterscotch chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and miniature marshmallows until well coated.
Press evenly into pan using the back of spoon.
Cool. Heat shortening and milk chocolate chips in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth. Spread chocolate over cereal in pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Remove about 10 minutes before cutting.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/4-inch bars.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Clean roast thoroughly with a clean cloth soaked in vinegar. Trim away excess fat.
Coat roast with French dressing.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Three to four hours before serving time, brown roast on all sides in a heavy pan in hot oil.
Coat again with French dressing.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slice unpeeled orange, apple and lemon and attach slices to roast with toothpicks.
Cover tightly and bake in a 300° oven until tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Blend and let stand in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine.
Beat eggs, add zucchini, cheese and seasonings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine first 6 dry ingredients. Cut in grated orange rind and butter until coarse like cornmeal. Add sweet potato and buttermilk, just enough to moisten and make workable. Pat out to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 1 1/2-inch round biscuit cutter. Dock with fork 2 rows. Brush lightly with melted butter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes. Serve with thinly sliced country cured ham.

title: chili mac casserole
directions: In a large nonstick frypan, heat oil.
Add beef and stir to brown, then add onion, garlic, pepper and celery.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes (including juice), oregano and Italian seasoning.
Cover; reduce heat and cook about 20 minutes.
Add beans and macaroni.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes until heated through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pan, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off any fat. Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
To serve, top with shredded cheese and sour cream and serve with tortilla chips.

title: guacamole
directions: Halve and pit avocados; remove from skin with spoon.
Mash with other ingredients, combine thoroughly.
Chill 1 to 2 hours (if longer, avocado may start to discolor).
Serve as dip with chips.

title: angel wings (chrusty)
directions: Mix flour with butter, sugar, egg, vinegar and enough sour cream to work the batter into a soft dough.
Place the dough on a kneading board and roll out.
Cut in 2 x 4-inch strips.
Cut a hole in the middle of each strip, then pass one end of each strip through it to make a knot.
Fry Angel Wings in hot shortening (lard) until light brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when ready.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake until done at 300° to 350°.

title: prairie taco salad
directions: Brown beef.
Drain and add beans.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, onion, cheese, avocado, tomato and olives.
Add beef mix. Combine Miracle Whip, taco sauce and chili powder.
Pour over salad and toss.
Mix in broken Doritos to taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini casserole no. 1
directions: Mix
all
ingredients; pour into greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake,
uncovered,
at
for 30 to 40 minutes. You may save out a small amount of crumbs and shredded cheese to sprinkle on top before baking.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough mayonnaise to bind mixture (approximately 3 to 4 tablespoons).
Let chill at least 4 to 5 hours.
Use in thinly sliced spiced meat sausage or peppered beef, celery, tomato, etc.

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: Beat egg white.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and beat until stiff.
Stir in remaining sugar and ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: corn macque choux
directions: Cut corn off of the cobs, skimming the tops of the kernels, then scrape the juice out of the kernels.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a bowl put the salad oil, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, salt and sugar.
Beat with a beater 3 minutes.
Add the mayonnaise and beat 3 minutes more.
Add the poppy seed and beat until blended.
This dressing will not separate.
Yield:
About 2 cups. It is very good used on spinach salad (fresh).

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg.
Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Combine molasses and hot water.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, a small amount at a time, and beat after each addition until smooth.
Bake in well greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar.
Add everything else.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except 1 cup of oats.
Mix well.
Form into teaspoon-sized balls and roll in reserved oats.
Place on a cookie sheet coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: easy ham, green pea and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the noodles according to package, omitting the salt.
Meanwhile, in a
medium-size bowl, combine the flour, mustard, sage, nutmeg and pepper; slowly whisk in the milk and set aside.

When the noodles are done, drain and combine with the ham and peas; add the milk mixture and stir well. Spoon into an ungreased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with the bread crumbs and dot with the margarine.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 10 minutes longer or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: bean soup
directions: Add enough water to cover plus 3 inches over.
Cook about 4 hours.
Watch in case it needs more water.
Take ham bone and celery stalks out and skim fat.
Add tomatoes and parsley. Continue to cook a few more hours.

title: granna settle's corn pudding
directions: Place butter in pan the pudding is to be cooked in and melt. Mix ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Put in preheated oven at 450°.
Cook for 15 minutes until set.
Test by inserting knife in center of pudding.
Brown at 500°.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Butter baking dish and preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake 1 hour.

title: sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and let stand 3 to 4 hours in cold water. Boil mixture. Cut up cucumbers and pack in sterilized jars. Pour mixture over cucumbers. Seal.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill before serving. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and leave whole.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers each night for 4 nights.
On the fifth night, cut up cucumbers and cover with a boiling solution of the rest of the ingredients.
Let stand for 3 days.
Then bring all to a boil. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: tortellini with shrimp
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Keep warm.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in melted butter until translucent but not browned (about 5 minutes).
Add shrimp.
Saute 3 minutes until shrimp turns pink.
Add tomatoes and creme fraiche.
Remove from heat.
Toss shrimp mixture with tortellini and Parmesan cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into an ovenproof serving dish.
Sprinkle top with additional Parmesan cheese and drizzle with olive oil.
Can be made ahead of time. Heat at 325° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: coconut fudge
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and milk.
Let come to a full boil.
Boil 2 minutes 45 seconds.
Do not stir while cooking.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Beat. Add coconut and a few pecans.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix egg, milk and oil and add all at once to dry ingredients.
Line muffin tins with liners or grease and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Beat all ingredients on low speed scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl, one minute. Pour into loaf pan, bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan. Cool completely before slicing. Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let all cheese set to room temperature.
Mix together and form into a ball.
Cool in refrigerator.
Roll in chopped nuts or parsley.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix cream of celery soup with liquid.
Add dried bread crumbs, beaten eggs, onion and lemon juice.
Grease bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: linguine with triple red pepper sauce(double ingredients for 2)
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, bell pepper and crushed red pepper; saute until bell pepper softens, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add roasted peppers, linguine and 1/2 cup Parmesan; toss until coated.
Season with salt and pepper.
Divide pasta among 4 plates.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve, passing additional Parmesan cheese separately.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Combine dates, water and soda.
Let stand.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt, cocoa and flour.
Add dates mixture alternately with the dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips and the chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: big apple pancake
directions: Should be served warm; probably won't last long enough to get cold.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water.
Add cold water.
Put in ice cups and freeze.

title: stilton-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and pat dry with a paper towel.
Remove stems gently.
In a bowl, toss mushrooms with lemon juice; drain.
Add 2 tablespoons melted butter; toss with mushrooms.
In a small bowl, beat the egg; add cheese.
Spoon this into mushroom caps equally. Broil mushroom caps 8 to 10 inches from heat source for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown; remove.
Use tongs to place on a serving platter.
Serve hot.

title: granny harrell's liniment
directions: Mix well.
Always use equal parts.
Store in a glass jar or bottle.

title: oysterettes
directions: Mix dressing, oil and spices well. Pour over crackers.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 300° oven until sauce is absorbed. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in greased and floured oblong pan.
Cool.

title: kentucky franks
directions: Combine
everything
in saucepan or crock-pot.
Add hot dogs (weenies) and let simmer 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: peppercorn chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound with flat edge of mallet to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Sprinkle with peppercorns.
Heat heavy nonstick skillet.
Add butter and chicken. Cook, turning once, until chicken is done, about 5 minutes. Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: tomato and okra
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray; add oil and saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 7 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Bring to boil sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° until custard thickens and pie shell browns.
Cool and serve.

title: pork and beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in a 10-inch skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until mixture is bubbly.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan lightly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil first three ingredients, then cool.
Add remaining ingredients to marinade and refrigerate overnight.	Can be served as an appetizer or as a vegetable with dinner.
Gets better with age and keeps well.

title: russian nut balls(christmas cookie)
directions: Combine in order. Form balls 1-inch in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; no longer than 10 minutes. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix together the cake mix and vanilla.
In a saucepan boil water; add the cake mixture and blend well.
Set aside to cool.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel apples.
Cut into	eighths
and
arrange in pastry shell. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup with flour.
Cut butter into sugar and flour until crumbly.
Sprinkle over
apples.
Bake
at 450° about 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°
and
bake
30	minutes or until apples are tender.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine pineapple juice and water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, lemon juice, lemon peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens, slightly.
Add sour cream, stir until mixed thoroughly.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 8 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with strawberries if desired.
Serve.

title: pie crust(stir in pastry)
directions: Pour milk and oil together, but don't stir.
Add all at once to sifted flour.
Stir with fork until blended.
Form into a ball. Divide in halves.
Roll each half out between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Makes two 8-inch pie crusts.

title: easy cake mix cookies
directions: Mix with spoon.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first six items.
Cut in butter until crumbs to size of small peas.
Arrange apples in buttered 9 x 11-inch baking pan. Cover with raisins.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over top, covering completely, and gently press down.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Chill pie shell while making filling.
Blend eggs, sugar and salt.
Add flavorings.
Gradually stir in the scalded milk.
Pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Heat oil and brown meat.
Add salt.
Add onion, garlic, green peppers and hot peppers.
Pour in beef stock.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Blend water, soy sauce and cornstarch. Stir into broth.
Cook until liquid is translucent.
Serve on rice.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cook chicken, remove skin and bone. Put chicken and broccoli in baking dish.
Spread soup over top.
Sprinkle cheese over all. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: apple-date spread
directions: In a bowl, beat together cream cheese and milk.
Stir in chopped pecans, apples and dates. Garnish with apple slices. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, salt, buttermilk and flour. Make paste of red food coloring, cocoa and vanilla; stir into batter. Mix soda and vinegar; stir in batter but do not beat. Pour into 3 greased layer pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon lei chiffon cake
directions: Bake our lemon chiffon cake mix in tube pan as directed.
Cool. Cut cake in half horizontally.
Fill cake with Pineapple Filling (following).
Frost with our lemon fluff frosting mix.
Make a wreath on top of cake with fresh mint leaves or green leaf gumdrops.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Melt cheese in microwave and place in crock-pot on low setting.
Add chili and ground beef to crock-pot.
Stir in cup of milk.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking after mixing all ingredients together.

title: spaghetti squash pie
directions: Microwave squash on high for 6 minutes per pound. Make sure there are several slits in the skin of the squash.
After cooled, cut open and remove seeds. Throw away.
Use a fork and remove the squash pulp.

title: chili beans and rice(makes a great side dish for burrito casserole)
directions: In a
microwave-safe
dish, place water, uncooked rice, onion, green pepper, bouillon granules and chili powder.
Cook covered on High for
to
minutes or until vegetables are tender and water
is
absorbed.
Stir
in beans.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3
minutes
or
until heated through.
Stir and sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook until thick.
Pour into jars; process for 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: french green beans with water chestnuts
directions: Cook beans according to directions on package.
Add drained water chestnuts and heat thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana crush
directions: Combine bananas and lemonade in blender.
Blend until smooth. Combine banana mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into plastic freezer containers.
Freeze until slushy.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: crock-pot meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, onion (chopped fine), Worcestershire sauce and milk. Roll into balls and bake at 350° until brown. Drain on paper towels. In a crock-pot, combine catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Add drained meatballs and simmer.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Place in Crock Pot in this order:
cut into bite size pcs potatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Mix together and pour over all:
1 can tomato soup, 1 can water, salt and pepper to taste. Cook on High 4 hours, then Low 1-2 hours. or on high for 5 hours. Add some frozen peas just before serving.

title: banana pop
directions: Peel and cut banana in half crosswise.
Slide popsicle stick into cut end of banana half.
Roll in wheat germ.
Stand in jar. Place in freezer.

title: apple pie delight
directions: In a large bowl, mix all dry ingredients and add apples and toss until apples are evenly coated with mixture.
Place apples in bottom crust and add dashes of margarine over apples.
Cover apples with top crust.
Cut slits in top crust and seal top and bottom crusts together around edges.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat and bake 30 more minutes at 350°.

title: boneless chicken breasts with broccoli
directions: Cut chicken breasts into cubes.
Cut broccoli into flowerets. Heat 1/4 cup oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute the chicken with the garlic, shallot, salt and pepper until lightly browned.

title: honey dressing for fruit
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, paprika, celery seed and salt.
Stir in honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Very slowly pour salad oil into mixture, beating constantly with rotary beater.
Makes 2 cups.

title: happy easter eggs
directions: Beat! Beat! Beat!
Can be divided to add coconut, peanut butter, fruit or nuts.
Form into Easter eggs, large and small. Keep refrigerated until you coat.
Melt almond bark.
Dip eggs. Place on waxed paper to harden.
Decorate with cake icing.

title: nuts over you
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter chips, unsweetened chocolate and marshmallows. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until well blended and the mixture thickens and begins to leave sides of pan. Remove from heat, fold in peanuts and raisins. Spread mixture evenly in a lightly buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill. Cut in squares. Makes about 36 pieces.

title: bundt coffee cake
directions: In a large electric mixer bowl, add cake mix, pudding mix, oil and water.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Turn mixer to half speed and mix for 8 minutes; add vanilla.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon together.
Grease but do not flour Bundt pan. Sprinkle small amount of cinnamon, sugar-nut mix on bottom.
Add cake mixture to cover, alternating the batter, cinnamon sugar-nut mix.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 50 minutes.
When done, let stand inverted on cooling rack.

title: deviled cracker
directions: Cream butter with Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on saltines. Sprinkle with the paprika.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Mix buttermilk and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add flour, eggs, salt and flavoring.
Bake at 325°.

title: chili egg fajitas
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Scramble egg and mash fine, then combine eggs, cheese, chili, hamburger, garlic and jalapenos (optional).
Blend in saucepan on medium heat.
Spoon in flour tortillas; serve hot or at room temperature.

title: theresa shea's cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix until well combined.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped candied cherries.

title: swedish meat loaf wellington
directions: Mix all ingredients except rolls.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in shallow pan at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Spoon off fat. Separate one package of crescent rolls.
Place over loaf top and down sides.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake, covered, in greased casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: lemon lime trifle
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve the gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in 1 cup lemonade.
Chill until soft-set, about 2 to 3 hours. Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with spoon, then add wet ingredients. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325°.

title: spinach-cheese appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Heat oil over medium-high heat in small skillet.
Add onion. Cook and stir until translucent. Beat eggs in large bowl; stir in onion, Feta cheese, spinach, parsley and oregano. Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: no-knead roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar salt and half of flour. Beat for 2 min.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth, let rise until double in bulk, poke down, shape into rolls.
Place on lightly oiled pan.
Let rise 30-45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until tops are brown.

title: noodle mix
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Combine soup, onion, garlic and parsley.
Add water, stir.
Then combine with noodles. Serves 6.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Mix remaining ingredients; dip onion rings into mixture and deep fry 2 or 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain and salt.

title: white bread
directions: Heat milk, but don't boil.
Set off and add sugar, salt and shortening.
Let cool to lukewarm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Pour melted butter over brown sugar, pecans and corn flakes. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: olive dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Mix in rest of ingredients.

title: poor man's rouladen(german)
directions: Flour meat, then brown in the shortening, browning on both sides.
Add water to cover.
Slice pickle; lay on meat.
Add pickle juice also.
Cover; cook on low fire for 30 to 45 minutes, after adding 1 cup of water and 1 bouillon cube.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
The pickle juice tenderizes the meat and gives the juices in pan a special flavor.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cool completely.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 6 hours. Drain before serving.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt Crisco, add milk, sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved in small pan on stove.
Pour into a large mixing bowl to cool.
Add yeast to warm water and add a small amount (1/2 tsp.) sugar, When mixture has cooled, add 2 cups flour then eggs and yeast.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Put on a floured table and fold in until it does not stick to your fingers.
Be careful and not add too much flour.
The dough needs to be soft.
Dough may be divided and use half now and put the other in a floured gallon zip lock bag and put in the refrigerator.
Shape dough into rolls and place in a warm place until it doubled in bulk.
As dough in the refrigerator rises, punch down and reseal bag.
When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator, make into rolls, brush tops with butter and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.

title: henry's beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spoon into greased muffin tins and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune bread
directions: *Can use 2 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup wheat germ as an alternate use.

title: best ever blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl and make well in center. Combine egg and milk.
Melt shortening; cool slightly.
Add to egg mixture.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Drop batter from tablespoon into greased muffin pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed on box and cool.
Mix vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk.
Begin layering.

Cut cake in half, crumble one half in punch bowl, add 1/2 pudding mixture to the top of crumbled cake, add 1/2 can pie filling, add 1/2 can crushed pineapple, add 1/2 tub Cool Whip and add 1/2 package pecans.
Then begin another layer with the other 1/2 of the ingredients:
cake, pudding, pie filling, pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.

title: spinach dip
directions: If using frozen spinach, thaw and squeeze out water.
Combine all ingredients (except bread) and chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours before serving.
Shredded carrots can be added for more color.
Serve in a hollowed-out loaf of bread.
Use vegetable sticks or bread cubes for dipping.
Makes 3 1/2 cups of dip. Contains 20 calories and .6 gram of fat per 1/4 cup.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients for ham loaf.
Make into a loaf or meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: liver sausage ball
directions: Mix liver sausage with 1 1/4 packages of the cream cheese and the onion, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and horseradish.
Shape into a ball.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Beat egg in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix all other ingredients (except chicken) together.
Cut chicken up into pieces and dip in egg, then in mixture until well coated.
Fry in deep fryer until crispy.

title: layered salad
directions: In a salad bowl or large oblong casserole dish, layer all the ingredients in the order in which they are listed.
Do not stir. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken breast with wine
directions: Bone and skin chicken breast.
Split and pound thin.
Dredge chicken breast in flour.
Brown chicken in oil and butter.
Add apple cider, wine, parsley and marjoram.
Cover and simmer over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and keep warm.
Increase heat and boil sauce for 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Serve sauce over the chicken.
Serves 2.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all this together in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple and pecan cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until real creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix and sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in chopped apple and blend well.
Add pecans and mix by hand, then spoon into greased tube pan, pressing with hands.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until it springs back when touched.
Cool in pan before placing on cake plate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: pumpkin dessert squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 7 ingredients and pour over cake mix in pan.
Mix the last 3 ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and oil, then water. Mix well by hand.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and blend. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Shape into a roll; wrap in wax paper and chill for several hours.
Cut into slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: becky's georgia fried grits
directions: Cook grits according to box, any amount.
After cooking, pour into pie plate or flat bowl.
Let set until cold.
Cut into pie shaped pieces.
Dip in beaten eggs and fry in oil until brown. Tastes like fish.

title: divinely decadent fudge cake
directions: In a large pan bring corn syrup and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat; add chocolate and stir until melted.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour and nuts.
Grease and flour one 9-inch cake pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on rack.
Pour glaze over cake; let stand 1 hour.
Garnish with pecans or walnuts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1 tablespoon of sugar in water.
Cut shortening into flour.
Combine buttermilk, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture and remaining sugar to flour.
Place in airtight container; refrigerate or roll out on a floured board. Place on a greased pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix the wet ingredients, then mix together.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup melted margarine, grated onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Fold in potatoes.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole or 2 smaller casseroles.
Stir remaining butter into crushed cracker crumbs and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, less if poured into 2 casseroles. One pan can be frozen and used later.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake(world war i)
directions: Boil
water,
sugar,
shortening and raisins for 5 minutes. Cool
until
shortening
starts
setting
on
surface, turning white.
Then
beat
in
flour sifted with salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg,
ginger
and
cloves.
Bake
in greased and floured 9
x 12-inch pan for 50 or 60 minutes at 325°.
Frost with
plain powdered sugar frosting, thinned with just enough water
or canned
milk to make a spreadable frosting, vanilla added
if desired.
When in a hurry just sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top before baking and eliminate icing all together.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients and form into one-inch balls. Chill.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Keep warm.
Dip chilled balls with fork into chocolate paraffin mixture.
Lay onto wax paper to set.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together; add oil and mix.
Add flour, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after cooled to room temperature.

title: tofu mayonnaise
directions: Place all ingredients into blender bowl.
Blend, adding water as needed.
Use a start and stop routine until smooth.
For sour cream, use 6 tablespoons of lemon juice and less honey.

title: pepper dip
directions: I put a little sour cream to make it softer.

title: homemade peanut butter cup bars
directions: Mix melted margarine, graham crackers, peanut butter and confectioners sugar together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate overnight, then cut into squares.

title: corn crisp chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in evaporated milk.
Roll in mixture of corn flakes and salt (a little pepper if you wish).
Place chicken, skin side up, in foil-lined shallow 9 x 13-inch baking pan. For added flavor, drizzle with melted butter or margarine. Do not cover pan while baking.
Cover loosely with foil if less crisp crust is desired.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags. cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Combine tea and fruit juices, add sugar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ice water and ginger ale.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs until fluffy. Cut butter into small pieces. Mix all ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fluffy lemon fruit pie
directions: Spread half of the cherry pie filling on bottom of crust. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese with wire whisk until smooth. Gradually beat in milk until well blended. Add pudding mix. Beat until smooth. Gently stir in 1/2 tub whipped topping. Spread over cherry pie filling on bottom of crust. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding mixture. Spoon remaining cherry pie filling over whipped topping layer. Refrigerate 3 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir.
Then bake for an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: mom's pate
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1/2 pound butter until softened. Add livers and saute until lightly browned but still rare.
Blend in batches (1/3 at a time).
Add remaining 1/2 pound melted butter, brandy, whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Strain through a fine sieve.
Add pureed truffle, if desired.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart terrine.
Chill. Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Place cooked broccoli in bottom of large baking dish.
Layer meat on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over meat and spread mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbling.

title: country giblet gravy
directions: Remove turkey from roasting pan.
Pour pan drippings into large measuring cup, fat will rise to top.
Return 4 tablespoons fat to roasting pan.
Discard remaining fat.
Reserve broth (about 1 1/2 cups).

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery for 7
minutes in salt water and drain.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle water chestnuts on top.
Brown almonds in butter.
Crush crackers and add to buttered almonds. Pour soup over celery.
Top with almond-crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: yankee fruit salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling; add jello.
Stir and let cool. Crush pimento with cream cheese and stir into gelatin mixture; add celery and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Combine thawed strawberries and gelatin; set aside.
Mix unsifted flour with other ingredients. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.

title: marinated italian green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Servings:
1/2 cup each; 25 calories; 0 fat.

title: chicken montpelier
directions: Cut each breast in half.
Place each between waxed paper and flatten with mallet to about 1/8 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; set aside.
Whip the butter until fluffy and stir in the herbs.
Cut cheese lengthwise into 8 pieces.
Spread herb butter on cheese and on breasts, saving some butter for sauce. Place a stick of cheese on each breast and roll up, tucking in ends to seal.
Coat rolls in flour.
Dip in eggs, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in a flat baking dish and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in thick or heavy pot.
Add milk to moisten.
Add remainder of milk gradually, stirring continuously. Add remaining ingredients.
Place on burner, medium-high, stirring constantly.
Cook for 20 minutes or until it won't boil up.

title: cabbage and cheese casserole
directions: Mix cornflakes and butter; reserve small amount.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Steam cabbage and onion for 10 minutes.
Drain. Place on top of cornflakes.
Mix milk, soup and mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with remaining cornflakes.
Bake at 350° until bubbles and brown.

title: southern cole slaw
directions: Mix together and pour over 1 quart finely chopped cabbage.

title: rick's famous chili
directions: Brown ground beef with Flavor Glo seasoning mix and place in a 2-quart cooker with remaining ingredients.
Turn burner on high until it starts to boil, then turn burner down to low or simmer for an hour.
Chili goes best with the Famous Peanut Butter Sandwich.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in soup pot over medium heat. If using onions, saut onions in the butter until translucent; add flour and stir and cook over low for about 1 minute. Gradually add 2 cups of milk, stirring constantly and heat through. Add more milk as needed to obtain a creamy consistency. Add cheese if desired. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: liver sausage pate
directions: Cut liver sausage into chunks.
Heat beef broth until hot, remove; add 1 package of gelatine.
Let cool.
Add liver sausage and onion.
Put in blender and whip until pureed.
Put into small containers or serving dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and pour over vegetables and let set in refrigerator a few hours or overnight before serving.
Just before serving, add sunflower seeds.

title: porcupine cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 1/2-inch paper liners in 24 muffin cups.
Prepare, bake and cool cupcakes following package directions.
Frost cupcakes with chocolate frosting.
Place sliced almonds upright on each cupcake to decorate as a porcupine.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Wash strawberries; remove stems if desired.
Drain well; dry on paper towels.
Combine butter, corn syrup and salt, blending well; stir in powdered sugar.
Knead sugar mixture until smooth; chill 30 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(crustless)
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth, 1 minute in a blender on high or 2 minutes with hand mixer. Pour into greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/2) and bake at 350° until knife inserted into the center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: leona lowrie's fudge frosting cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the eggs, oil and sour milk.
Stir together and add vanilla and water.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
When cool, cover with Fudge Frosting.

title: link sausage and cabbage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add sausage and brown both sides.
Remove sausage and keep warm.
Add cabbage and seasonings; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is soft.
Return sausage to skillet.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and add milk and beaten egg.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot grease.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix the turkey or chicken, soups, water chestnuts, vegetables and 1 cup of broth.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and margarine; pour over mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, mixing well. Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cloud 9 ambrosia salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine the mix, eggs and cherry filling.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir together in large bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In separate bowl, stir together pumpkin, corn oil and water.
To this mixture, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Add pumpkin mixture and stir just until flour is moist.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, covered, then for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and pour in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: caramel corn
directions: Fill large roasting pan with 7 to 8 quarts popped unsalted popcorn.
Mix ingredients (all except soda).
Boil for 5 minutes. Add soda and mix; pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on wax paper or Teflon sheet.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns; mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: stir-fry steak and vegetables
directions: Trim any fat from steak.
Cut across grain in thin diagonal strips, about 2 inches long.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, honey, ginger and garlic.
Toss with steak and marinate 30 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Prepare vegetables.
Heat oil in large skillet (or wok).
Drain meat, saving marinade.
Add meat to skillet.
Cook quickly over high heat, stirring constantly, just until meat starts to brown.
Avoid overcooking.
Remove meat; lower heat to moderately high.
Add onions, stir-fry 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms and celery; cook 2 minutes. Add reserved marinade; heat 1 minute.
Add meat and pineapple; stir until heated.
Serve at once with rice.
Serves 2.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large pot, cook sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt until boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir to mix.
Pour syrup over popcorn in a large bowl.
Toss to coat.
Pour popcorn on 2 cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
When done, spread popcorn out to cool.

title: mincemeat-pumpkin pie
directions: Spread a layer of mincemeat in the bottom of an unbaked pie crust.
Finish filling with pumpkin pie filling.
Bake as for pumpkin pie.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add sour cream.

title: broccoli cranberry nut salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Add cranberries and sugar last.

title: beef soup(borscht)
directions: In a large kettle of water seasoned with salt and pepper, simmer the meat until tender.
Remove meat and cut up in bite sized pieces.
Return meat to kettle.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Add a tablespoon of sour cream just before serving. Serve in large bowls with buttered French rolls.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream Crisco, salt and 1/4 cup sugar until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and egg yolks; mix in flour. Pat dough into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Bake 15 minutes. Spread hot crust with preserves. Top with coconut. Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar until peaks form. Spread over coconut; bake 25 minutes. Cool completely before cutting. Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: world's easiest ice cream
directions: Stir buttermilk into jam.
Pour into refrigerator tray. Freeze until firm.
Cut up frozen mixture and place in chilled mixer bowl.
Whip with electric mixer until fluffy.
Return to tray.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Spoon into sherbet dishes. Garnish with fresh strawberries and mint leaves.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Before starting, pour water over dates and let cool.

title: pizza crescents
directions: Roll out crescent. Spoon sauce over top. Sprinkle cheese over top. Place 3 pepperoni onto each crescent. Roll up and place on ungreased
baking sheet. Cook as directed on crescent package.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in salt and egg.
Sift flour and soda together and stir in also, adding mashed bananas last.
Use 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding dates and nuts last. Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients and cook 1 hour.
Mix water and cornstarch; add to mix and cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour in jars and hot bath for 10 minutes.

title: cowpoke chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste and beef broth until smooth.
Add kidney beans and seasonings.
Add lima beans.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Stew chicken and remove all bones.
Cut into small pieces. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bring to boil the chicken broth and can of chicken soup.

title: crabmeat dip(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart dish, saute butter, onion, parsley and celery on High for 4 minutes in microwave.
Stir in cream cheese.
Microwave on High 1 minute, if cheese is not softened.
Add garlic powder, Tabasco sauce, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Fold crabmeat in gently.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Serve with Melba rounds.

title: heloise's meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly for 1 minute.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: rachel's meal-in-a-muffin
directions: Combine oats, milk and applesauce.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add egg, oil and sugar.
Mix. Stir in dry ingredients, then carrots and raisins.
Bake in greased muffin pan at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: curried corn and tomato soup
directions: Heat butter in saucepan; add onion.
Cook until wilted, then add garlic; stir.
Add curry powder and flour.
Stir.
Add the tomato, chicken stock and bay leaf, stirring.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Pour soup into container of food processor or electric blender.
Blend as thoroughly as possible.
Reheat and add the corn.
Bring to the boil.
Remove from the heat and stir in yogurt. Serve sprinkled with chopped chives.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook for about 2
minutes after it comes to a hard boil; then add
2 teaspoons vanilla, 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups oatmeal (1 minute oatmeal).
Put on tray to cool.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix crackers, milk, eggs, salt and cream corn.
Add crackers on top.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or 350°.
Double batch will bake for 2 hours.

title: countertop sweet pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers, put in jar.
Dissolve salt in cold water, enough to cover.
Let stand for 4 days.
Drain off salt water.
Wash 3 times.
Slice back into jar, in chunks or thick slices.
Add alum and water to cover.
Let set 24 hours.
Drain and rinse 3 times.
Put back in jar.
Cover with white vinegar. Let set 10 days.
Drain off vinegar and discard.
Add 2 teaspoons pickling spice tied in cloth.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Shake or stir. Add 3 cups sugar in 2 more days.
Shake after each addition. Cover with lid and store on counter.

title: cranberry arctic freeze
directions: Mix well with mixer cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add cranberry sauce and mix.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Cover and freeze.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use Pam in 8-inch square pan.
Mix sugar and cocoa in bowl. Make a puddle.
Add butter and milk. Cook in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Add nuts and vanilla and mix.
Pour in dish. Put in refrigerator for 1 hour before cutting.

title: stuart's banana pie
directions: You will need a 10-inch glass pie plate.

title: squash relish
directions: Wash and stem squash; scrape out seed.
Grate squash.
Chop or grate peppers.
Add salt.
Drain.
Add remaining 5 ingredients. Mix and bring to a good boil.
Stir and place in sterilized pint or half-pint sized jars.
Seal.

title: baked corn
directions: Cover with bread crumbs and bake until tests done, like custard.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and 3 squares of chocolate. Remove from heat and blend in 3 cups sugar, 1/4 teaspoon of salt and vanilla.
Mix well and add evaporated milk.
Return mixture to heat, mix and cook until all sugar is dissolved, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Makes 1 quart. Refrigerate.

title: magic lemon meringue pie(makes an 8-inch pie.)
directions: Put Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, lemon rind or lemon extract and egg yolks into mixing bowl; stir until mixture thickens.
Pour filling into chilled crumb crust or cooled pastry shell.

title: baked catfish
directions: Place fillets in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour lemon juice over all.
Sprinkle evenly with All Seasoning.
Top with butter. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In frying pan, add refried beans and taco seasoning mix to ground beef; cook for 10 minutes.
In casserole dish, layer ground beef mixture, cream cheese and salsa and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: frankfurters and noodles
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix together in bowl, the soup, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and sauteed onion and green pepper.
Slice frankfurters in quarter slices or round slices.

title: diabetic cocoa mix
directions: For cocoa mix, in a storage container, combine dry milk, cocoa powder, sugar substitute and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Cover and store in a cool, dry place for up to 8 weeks.

title: betty's meat pie
directions: Brown crumbled meat in large skillet; drain off fat.
Add onion, salt, pepper, chili powder, kidney beans and corn; let simmer, covered, for about 15 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Stir; do not beat.
Batter will be lumpy.
Divide batter equally between 6 or 8 greased custard cups or popover tins. Put into cold oven. Set temperature to 450°. Bake 30 minutes. Resist the impulse to peek!
Batter can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: cheese omelet in microwave(servings: 2.  preparation time: 9 minutes.)
directions: Place the egg whites into a large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed until soft peaks form.
In smaller bowl, place the egg yolks and, using the same beaters, beat yolks, mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons of water.
Gently pour yolk mixture over whites and fold in carefully.
Melt margarine in 9-inch pie plate and swirl to coat inside.
Carefully pour eggs into pie plate.
Microwave at Medium (half power) for 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese over eggs and microwave at Medium for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Sprinkle with chopped chives and olives, then quickly run a spatula around sides and bottom of dish.
Fold half of omelet over the other half.
Slide onto serving plate.

title: low-fat salad dressing
directions: Combine dressing mix with mayonnaise and mix thoroughly using wire whisk.
Add buttermilk, slowly, stirring constantly, until well mixed.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in brown mixing beaker or a small bowl. Blend with brown hand hand blender until thoroughly combined.
Use as a dressing for mixed greens, spinach or fruit salads.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until rice is tender.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce. Drain and flake the crab meat. Add crab and onion to mixture. Place in 8-inch pie plate and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Serve with crackers.

title: frozen corn
directions: Combine corn and ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool, package and freeze.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy. Slowly add sugar, beating until thick. Add oil and vanilla. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Mix into egg mixture. Stir in walnuts. Arrange apples in bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour batter over apples. Spread to cover. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: thai chicken salad
directions: In bowl, whisk salad oil, next five ingredients and 1 tablespoon of water.
Stir in green onions.
Add chicken pieces and toss to coat with dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 350 calories and 27 g fat per serving.

title: icebox gingersnap cake
directions: Grind or crush gingersnaps.
Put half in 11 x 7-inch pan. Melt margarine with
confectioners sugar.
Add beaten eggs to sugar, then mashed bananas and drained pineapple.
Put on top of crumbs; sprinkle with remaining half of gingersnap crumbs.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter; add sifted dry ingredients and stir in.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscrosses.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Blend Ranch dressing mix and all of the seasonings with the oil, make sure it is mixed very well; pour over crackers and stir well.
Store 24 hours to blend.

title: cheese egg balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix all together. Form balls and roll in grated Parmesan cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour one large bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; keep refrigerated.
(Refrigerate for 1/2 hour before using.)

title: tuna celery bake
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain. Combine soup and milk. Alternate layers of noodles and tuna in greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Pour soup over top. Top with buttered crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Garnish with stuffed olive slices and parsley.
Enjoy! Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix sugar, Eagle Brand, butter and vanilla in large bowl. Roll cherries on paper towels until very dry.
Wrap dough around cherries.
Refrigerate for easier dipping.

title: creamy broccoli au gratin soup
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Add water, rice and seasoning packets.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Combine flour and dry mustard in a small bowl.
Gradually add about 1/2 cup of the broth, stirring until smooth.
Stir remaining broth, flour mixture and milk into rice mixture.
Heat to a simmer, stirring occasionally.
Continue simmering until slightly thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add milk and egg yolks, stirring well.
Combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, lemon rind and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in 1 cup butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yeast mixture, stirring well.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large mixing bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour and remaining ingredients at low speed until blended. Scrape bowl often. Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes or until smooth. Reduce speed to low; add remaining flour 1 cup at a time until dough is very stiff. If using a small mixer, the last flour may be stirred or kneaded in by hand. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush cookie press lightly with oil. Press dough with desired cookie press or use a fork to press. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned at edges. Cool 5 minutes on sheet. Cool completely on rack. Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except cornbread mix.
Then add the cornbread mix.
Pour into greased oblong pan. Bake in 375 degree oven for about 25 minutes.

title: eggplant - stuffed
directions: Remove eggplant meat from skin, leaving shell that's 1/2-inch thick.
Save shells for stuffing.

title: chewy pecan squares
directions: In top of double boiler, heat (slightly) beaten eggs in brown sugar.
Over
boiling
water, cook, stirring constantly until thickened,
about
minutes.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and
add
to thickened mixture along with the vanilla extract. Pour
into
buttered
x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at
350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When completely cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: sweet and sour vegetable salad
directions: Cook and cool vegetables; add onion, celery and pepper.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In a bowl, combine the cake mix, eggs and extract. Add pie filling; mix well. Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: peppered cheese ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; shape mixture into a 5-inch ball.

title: sweet pickle slices(million dollar recipe)
directions: Soak cukes with salt in enough boiling water to cover.
Let soak overnight.
Next morning, drain off salty water.
After draining, add 2 tablespoons alum to enough cold water to cover. Let stand overnight and next morning, drain.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar, 1 cup water and all of spices listed.
Bring to boil; add cukes.
When boiling point is reached again, pack in jars and seal.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel all fruits and chop up. Add sugar, coconut, raisins and marshmallows. Pour over chopped fruit. Mix well. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Mix well and stir in tight container.
Keep refrigerated.
Let stand about 1 week before serving.
Mix sugar to taste if you like it sweet; or more vinegar if you like it sour.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: Cut bacon into small slices. Fry bacon and chopped onion. Add flour to bacon grease and make a gravy with milk. After gravy is made, add frozen peas and mushrooms.
Simmer until thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: big bean pot
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven, saute bacon and onions until bacon is crisp and onions are tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: tomato pickles
directions: Quarter the tomatoes.
Slice onions.
Add to tomatoes in a large boiler.
Add peppers and spice.
Add vinegar and sugar until mixture just covers tomatoes.
(Start with small amount because when sugar melts, liquid will rise.) Let simmer until tomatoes are tender enough that a toothpick will stick through them easily. Let cook for a minute more.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: baked stuffed hamburger
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed for less moist stuffing.

title: pork steak bake
directions: Put layer of sliced potatoes in bottom of a greased roaster pan.
Add some salt, pepper, onion and a sprinkle of marjoram. Place pork steak on top with onion and seasonings.
Put more sliced potatoes on meat and use up seasonings and onion.
Mix soup with water; pour over all.
Cover; bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is soft.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in round or square cake pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crystal sticks
directions: Beat sugar lightly into eggs.
Do not overmix.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder; blend.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Spread evenly into a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars or sticks; roll in powdered sugar.
Keeps well; improves with aging.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with chopped parsley.

title: dump cake
directions: In the 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream while hot.

title: frosting or hot fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Stir in warm water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly to keep from lumping.
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.

title: my mom's hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Sift together into a bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, white sugar and 2 tablespoons of cocoa.
Stir in the milk and melted shortening.
Stir in the nuts and pour this mixture into a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 1 cup of brown sugar and 4 tablespoons of cocoa.
Pour 1 3/4 cups of very hot water slowly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
The cake will come to the top with a creamy, rich chocolate sauce forming on the bottom. Cut and serve the piece upside down on a plate and top with Cool Whip.

title: little river dirty rice
directions: Cook gizzards in water to cover until almost done; add livers.
Cook until tender.
Chop.
Heat butter in large skillet. Add green onions, onions, celery and green pepper.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are soft.
Add parsley flakes, garlic, giblets and ground beef.
Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes, stirring until well blended.
Add thyme, salt and pepper.
Add rice; mix well.
Spoon into casserole.
Bake in preheated 325° oven or about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter chip brownies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, cocoa and margarine.
Add dry ingredients. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with peanut butter chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange meringue pie
directions: Blend cornstarch, 3/4 cup sugar and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in hot water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat to low; cook and stir for 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Garnish with parsley flakes. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples and cut in halves.
Place 1/2 apple on each biscuit, rolled thin.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pinch dough together.
Turn pinched side down in dish. Prepare sauce.
Bring last four ingredients to a boil.
Pour this over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add pumpkin.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla extract. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add pecans and put into crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.
Cool before cutting.

title: crab louise
directions: Mix crabmeat, celery, onion and salt.
Set aside.

title: kielbasa and rice
directions: Brown Kielbasa in oil with peppers and onion. When brown add stewed tomatoes and seasoning. Serve over white rice. Quick and easy.

title: fried cabbage with hot banana peppers
directions: Chop cabbage.
Add banana peppers; cook until done.
This is delicious served with pork and slaw.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and corn syrup in a large microwave bowl.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Stir every 1 minute.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add soda.

title: date pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add nuts and dates rolled in flour. Add egg yolks.
Beat egg whites.
Separate and fold into the mixture.
Bake in slower oven (300°) about 20 minutes.
Cool and cover with whipped cream.

title: economical brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in a shallow pan, 7 x 11-inch or so in moderate oven.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Great for dipping strawberries, pineapple, kiwi, apples, etc.

title: irish coffee cake
directions: Dissolve coffee in whiskey; set aside.
Cream butter until smooth.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add sour cream, eggs, vanilla and coffee mixture.
Beat until well blended. Stir dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture.
Beat 3 minutes or until smooth.

title: oven stew
directions: Put all ingredients in covered pan.
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door while cooking.

title: walnut fingers
directions: Cream together butter, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Form into rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Chill 10 hours.
Slice thin.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: darta's chocolate cake
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together until liquid.
Mix next 4 dry ingredients in a mixer bowl.
Add liquid to dry mixture.
Beat in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla (pecans optional).
Cake batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Frost with Fudge Icing.
Serve hot with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add nectar gradually.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until done. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix together yogurt and Cool Whip.
Fold into pie crust and chill.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add frozen strawberries including juice.
Add bananas, pecans and crushed pineapple (well drained).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: caribbean delight
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 35 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all but barbecue sauce and soup together; roll into bite-size balls.
Place on a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix barbecue sauce and soup in pan; heat slightly.
Pour over meatballs in a chafing dish.
Replenish meatballs in existing sauce as they are needed.
Have toothpicks on hand for guests to serve themselves.
Makes about 200 meatballs.
(Can be made ahead and frozen.)

title: celery wagons
directions: Separate and clean stalks of celery.
Cut in 2-inch sticks. Cut 1/2-inch carrot slices.
Attach 4 carrot slices to celery, forming wheels with toothpicks.
Mix vegetable dip mix and sour half and half.
Fill celery wagons with vegetable dip.

title: chicken in wine in no time
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces to coat.
Brown chicken on all sides in skillet.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Add white wine, mushrooms and a little water. Cover; simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: ruby red slaw
directions: Combine syrup, vinegar, water, caraway seed, thyme and pepper; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes in a medium size pot.
Add cabbage that's sliced as cole slaw and the onion.
Simmer everything for another 15 minutes or until desired texture.
Serve warm or cold.

title: dipping red sauce for ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Makes 1/2 cup sauce.

title: kiwi and tangerine delight
directions: Peel kiwi and section tangerines and orange.
Open chilled fruit salad and pour in small glass serving dish.
Place serving dish in the middle of a plate and spread lettuce leaves around it, forming a bed of lettuce leaves.
Place kiwi, tangerine and orange slices around serving dish, alternating in a circle pattern. Chill and serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix crab meat, cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish or round glass pie dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chocolate cheese cupcakes
directions: Can be mixed all at one time.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Peel all vegetables.
Dice potatoes into bite size pieces. Slice carrots.
Slice onions into sections.
Shred cabbage.
Brown sausage lightly.
Add onions, cabbage and garlic; continue browning until vegetables are translucent.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice and herbs, potatoes and carrots.
Turn heat to low and cook two hours minimum or all day if you like.
Cook pasta al dente and add to soup right before serving.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Put flour, butter and salt in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Mix with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture looks like coarse meal.
With back of spoon, press mixture firmly onto bottom and halfway upsides of buttered 8-inch square pan. Drain peaches and save 1/2 cup syrup.
Arrange on top of mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Mix reserved syrup, evaporated milk and egg.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes more or until custard is firm except in the center.
Center will be firm after standing. Serve warm or cold.
Serves 9.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cook until tender all ingredients.
Add butter and serve hot.

title: homemade corn dogs
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add milk and oil.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Dry hot dogs; insert sticks and dip in cornmeal mixture.
Cook in oil until brown.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
May be frozen before using.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Rinse and dry cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a baking dish; drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: pasta and walnut fruit salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. In a small bowl, blend yogurt, honey and orange juice concentrate. In a large bowl, combine pasta and remaining ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add poppy seed.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate flour mixture and 1/2 cup milk to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 340° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom potato soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook mushrooms and onion in margarine 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, cook 2 minutes more.
Gradually add 5 cups water, cook, stirring, until mixture thickens and boils.
Add remaining ingredients except chives.
Cover, simmer 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with chopped chives.
Makes 8 servings, about 50 calories each.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo together until it looks like meal. Add nuts and mix.
Press into oblong baking dish approximately, 8 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding mix with 2 cups cold milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread rest of large Cool Whip on top and sprinkle a can of Angel Flake coconut over all.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar. Add pineapple juice. Chill. Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: zesty chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cool.
Save the chicken broth.
Remove the skin and cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Saute onions and green peppers in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth (add water if necessary).
Drain vermicelli, then add Cheez Whiz while hot, stirring well.
Next add onions, peppers, pimentos and soup.
Finally, add chicken.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix the Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add jello and mix well. Chop peaches and drain.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: hamburger quiche
