directions: Press the crescent roll dough in ungreased pie pan.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Place in pie shell. Combine mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch; mix until smooth. Stir in cheese and green onions.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine; combine next three ingredients and pour over margarine.
Pour filling or berries over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pie topping
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle over pie.
Makes a good topping for any fruit pie.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, vanilla and butter and mix well. Add beaten eggs.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions; drain.
Combine cheese, eggs and parsley for filling.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Fill shells with cheese filling and arrange in baking pan.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat cherry pie filling and water.
Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: baked beef stew
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Yield: 6 servings.
Diabetic Exchanges:
1 serving equals 4 lean meat, 1 1/2 starch, 1 vegetable; also 356 calories, 241 mg sodium, 97 mg cholesterol, 27 gm carbohydrates, 35 mg protein and 12 gm fat.

title: play doh
directions: Mix all ingredients together until it forms a ball, then knead until smooth.

title: pork roast
directions: Broil pork roast in pan 15 to 30 minutes until brown.
Stick cloves in pork roast and place in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over pork.
Cook on low heat 10 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 6 hours.

title: white rices(serves 4)
directions: Put water in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add oil and salt and cook until done.
Serve with chicken or beef.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together; use heaping tablespoon to a cup of hot water.
Makes a delicious drink.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies until coarse.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
To the rest of the cookie crumbs, add the melted butter; mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 can cream of chicken soup, 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup sour cream.
Turn into casserole and top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle can of French fried onion rings on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Serve with rice.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter peach cobbler
directions: Mix cereal and milk; let sit 3 minutes until soft.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; add egg and shortening to cereal and mix well.
Add flour mixture; stir with spoon.
Set this aside.
Mix in saucepan the peanut butter, margarine and brown sugar until smooth.
Add orange juice concentrate and peaches with juice (cut in big pieces).
Cook until it bubbles.
Spread in baking pan.
Drop first mixture by spoonfuls on top of this mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken chihuahua
directions: Simmer
chicken
in
seasoned
water (salt, garlic, bay leaf) 45
minutes
to an hour.
Save some broth.
Cool, debone and cut chicken
into
large bite sized pieces.
Saute onions and bell peppers in oil until tender but not brown.
Add soup, broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes, stirring thoroughly to remove soup lumps.
Heat to
boiling
point.
Spread half of the tortilla pieces in the bottom
of
the
oiled pan.
Spread half of the chicken pieces over
the
tortillas.
Pour
half
of the soup mixture over
the chicken.
Repeat these three layers.
Sprinkle shredded
cheese over
the top.
Lightly sprinkle the top with chili powder.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold topping into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm before serving.
If not used, can be frozen.
Wrap in sealing wrap after frozen.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Zucchini, zucchini, what to do with all the zucchini...

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except reserved margarine and bread crumbs.
Put into well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Add melted margarine.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pan free
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Store in refrigerator. Will last a long time.
No need to flour cake pan with this.
Let cake cool 10 minutes in upright position, then turn out.

title: tomato chicken aspic
directions: Heat V-8 and spices to a boil.
Add gelatin.
Pour over into casserole.
Chill until like egg white, then add cooked, diced chicken, celery, green pepper, green onions and green olives. Chill.
Serve with mayo.

title: stuffed ham and cabbage rolls in cream sauce
directions: Steam cabbage until tender; do not overcook.
Drain thoroughly.
Beginning at one end, place cabbage (about a large tablespoon) on rectangular ham.
Roll ham around cabbage and place seam-down in large baking dish.
Rolls are spaced evenly apart.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine meats, bread crumbs, eggs and milk; mix thoroughly. Form into balls.
Place in baking pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients and heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Baste frequently.

title: barbecue sauce(taste like chivettas)
directions: Beat egg and oil. Beat again and add other ingredients and stir. Store in fridge.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend until smooth.
Frost cake while warm.

title: french bread
directions: Whip egg whites and set aside.
Mix yeast, flour, sugar and salt together.
Add butter and water; mix until moist.
Add egg whites and mix.
Knead dough on floured surface about 10 to 15 minutes, until dough is elastic.
Put dough into lightly greased bowl and grease top lightly.
Cover bowl with clean cloth.
Let rise until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: potatoes parmesan
directions: Soak potatoes in cold water for 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes and shake in paper bag with flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and basil. Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan and bake for 30 minutes at 450° or until done.
Turn once to coat with margarine while baking.

title: john salestrom's hamburger pie
directions: Peel potatoes, boil and mash with 1/4 stick of butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: zucchini tacos
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan.
Add zucchini and squash, cook for 5-10 minutes.
Add seasoning and salt, stir & cook for 5-10 minutes, until soft.
While zucchini is cooking, prepare tortillas.	Lay flat on a hot, dry skillet until slightly browned. Fold in half and set aside.
Put zucchini into each prepared taco shell and top with cheese.

title: strawberry tarts
directions: Combine in bowl the cream cheese and slowly add and mix together the flour.
It will be hard to stir.
After mixture is complete, refrigerate for 1 hour.
Put small portions of pastry in tiny muffin tins.
Add a top of strawberry preserves and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and let cool.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; blend mayonnaise and water, stirring in a little at a time.
Add to flour mixture and blend together.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
To make 12 cupcakes, bake for about 15 minutes; test with a toothpick.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush 26 or so Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt the margarine and pour over the cookies.
Freeze for 20 minutes.
Next spread the ice cream over the cookies.
Freeze for 20 minutes.
Pour the can of syrup over the growing mess.
Top with the Cool Whip and crush 5 to 6 more cookies and sprinkle on top.
Freeze until 10 to 15 minutes before serving (and be sure no kids know where you are hiding it!).

title: chocolate intrigue(pound cake with chocolate center)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix.
Alternate mixing wet and dry ingredients, blending well after each addition.
Pour 2/3 of batter into a 10-inch tube pan, greased on the bottom.
Add to the remaining batter the chocolate syrup, soda and mint extract. Mix well and pour over white batter.
Do not mix together! Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool in the pan.

title: turkey burger
directions: Spread in hamburger buns and place in foil and heat 15 minutes at 350°.

title: braised red cabbage(serve with sauerbraten)
directions: Remove core and cut cabbage into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In large saucepan, combine cabbage, onion, apples, wine, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Add butter and stir until melted. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot tomato pickles
directions: Cook long enough to change color.
Put in jars and seal.
Do not overcook.
They should be crispy.

title: no fuss stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole bowl.
Cover with a lid and cook for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
An easy meal for a busy mom.

title: fried chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Mix flour and seasonings together.
Heat oil in skillet.
Dip chicken in egg mixture then in flour mixture.
Fry in hot oil until done.

title: fiesta pudding cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: culpepper's black-eyed pea soup
directions: Mix and let simmer about 5 minutes before adding cheese. Delicious!

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together and spread in 9 x 12-inch pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bar punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cakes in 2 (9-inch) round pans according to package directions.
Cool cakes and cut lengthwise.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Smash Heath bars.
Place first cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Put a layer of pudding, layer of Heath bars and a layer of Cool Whip.
Place second cake on top of Cool Whip.
Cut third cake in half.
Cut 1/2 into pieces to fill in the edges of the bowl.
Repeat the layers.
Repeat layers once more but reverse Heath Bars and Cool Whip ending with the Heath bars.

title: fettuccine with poppy seed
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain. Combine butter and next 4 ingredients; stir in sour cream. Combine fettuccine and sour cream mixture; add cheese and toss until fettuccine is coated.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: baked ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove crusts from bread; butter the slices with butter or margarine and place
8 buttered side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place ham and cheese over bread.
Top with remaining 8 slices of bread (butter side up).
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Pour melted butter over flakes.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard and pour over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 4 hours prior to baking.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add extracts one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Alternately add flour and eggnog; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
This is a large moist cake.
Very good at Christmastime.

title: pioneer cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with a small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Mix in Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add undrained pineapple.
Cool.
Blend in whipping cream (whipped) and mayonnaise.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or mixer.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple-cranberry mold
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple; add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling; pour over gelatin.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Turn into mold.
Chill until firm.
To unmold, dip into hot water for about 15 seconds, then invert.

title: apple sauce pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: seven week bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over the AllBran and set aside to cool.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown ground beef with diced onion and peppers.
Drain.
Add tomato juice and precooked macaroni.
Bring to boil; simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and horseradish together.
Spread a thin layer of the mixture on the sliced dried beef.
Roll into a log. Cut into bite size pieces.
Yields about 70 bite size pieces.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: Drain fruit; reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 3/4 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in reserved juice and ginger ale.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in fruit and spoon into lightly oiled 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold in salad dressing and marshmallows.
Spread on top of fruit mixture.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Chill well. Serves 12.

title: strawberry and sour cream ambrosia
directions: Reserve 4 whole strawberries; quarter remaining strawberries. Mix sugar with strawberries; let stand for 10 minutes.
Fold sugar mixture, marshmallows and coconut into sour cream.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Pile lightly into sherbet glasses.
Garnish with reserved whole strawberries.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cottage cheese and jello mold
directions: Add the Jell-O to the cottage cheese and mix well.
Add the Cool Whip.
Set in a mold or bowl and refrigerate to set.

title: ina's cheese cake
directions: Mix butter and crackers; save one cup for top.
Put rest in bottom of dish.

title: goulash
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch square pieces.
Heat oil and add the meat. When meat is browned on all sides, add the chopped onion and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add salt, paprika, pepper, tomato paste, caraway seed and flour or cornstarch.
Stir thoroughly, add water and simmer very slowly for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Stir in yogurt.
Remove from heat immediately.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Pare eggplant and slice into 1/8 inch slices. Spread 2 Tbsp. tomato sauce in the bottom of a 2 quart casserole. Layer half of eggplant, 1 can tomato sauce, half of oregano, and half of sharp cheese. Repeat layers. Cover. Microwave at high power 14-16 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 8 minutes. Add mozzarella cheese. Microwave at high power 1-2 minutes, or until cheese has melted.

title: caramels
directions: Put sugar, Karo and 1 pint cream in large pan.
Stir constantly until boiling.
Cook to 236° on candy thermometer.
Add second pint of cream and cook again to 236°.
Add third pint cream and parawax and cook to 242°.
Pour in buttered pans (large recipe).

title: lasagne rolls
directions: Cook lasagne pasta as directed on package.
Drain and rinse in cool water to cool.
Place on paper towel and pat dry.

Mix Ricotta, Parmesan cheese, half of the shredded Mozzarella, salt, egg, pepper, parsley and ground beef until well blended. Spread equal amounts of the mixture on the lasagne pasta and roll up. Spoon 1/2 cup sauce into bottom of baking dish.
Place rolls side by side. Spoon remaining sauce over rolls.
Top with remaining shredded Mozzarella and more grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Microwave for 20 minutes.
Stir in rice, soup, milk, half the cheese, and the onions.
Cook 6 minutes.
Stir.
Add the remaining cheese and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: raspberry truffle brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Beat together eggs and brown sugar.
Dissolve coffee crystals in water and add to egg mixture with chocolate.
Combine baking powder and flour and stir into chocolate mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick and easy fried oysters
directions: Put pancake mix into large shallow bowl.
Add oysters, a few at a time and toss lightly until well coated.
Shake off excess breading in wire basket.
Fry in deep fat at 350° until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Repeat process until all oysters are cooked.
Salt lightly and serve with cocktail or tartar sauce.
Makes 4 servings, about 8 oysters each.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder; add to mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Add apples and combine well.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice and water to boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine all other ingredients except cinnamon and nutmeg and add rice mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chickenetti
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes a lot.

title: chicken strips with mushrooms
directions: Lightly flour chicken strips.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter in nonstick frying pan.
Cook chicken until lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Slice mushrooms and cook with 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Remove from pan.
In 1 tablespoon butter cook minced garlic.
Add 1/2 can chicken broth, mushrooms and chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Recommended:
peas as vegetable and a loaf of garlic fresh bread.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix syrup and sugar together; bring to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter and butter.
Cook until peanut butter is melted.
Pour mixture over corn flakes and mix well.
Pour mixture in greased pan.
Spread evenly over the pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: stone soup
directions: For dry beans only:
rinse beans of any dirt or debris.
Add beans and bay leaf to a good-sized pot, fill with water about 3 inches over beans.
Boil for 2 minutes, remove from heat, cover, and let stand 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in oblong pan.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: fudge pies
directions: With a large wooden spoon mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt; add eggs, then chocolate and margarine.
Mix until smooth. Add milk gradually, then vanilla.
Sprinkle half of coconut and pecans in both bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over on top of coconut and pecans.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.
These pies are great for the holidays.

title: tagliarini
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add tomato juice and tomato paste.
Cook on low for 4 to 5 hours, then add cream-style corn and mushrooms.
Cook on low for 1/2 to 1 hour. Add noodles.
"Do not cook."
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake until brown.

title: very special poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all items except the poppy seed.
Beat ingredients for 5 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in the poppy seed and oil a Bundt pan.
Instead of flouring the pan, use cinnamon and sugar to cover the bottom and sides of pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check cake at 45 minutes to see if it's done.

title: graham cracker brittle
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with graham crackers. Bring margarine and sugar to a rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When bubbling has stopped, add nuts. Spoon over graham crackers.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut in strips.
Yields 48 to 70 pieces.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers on top and drizzle with 3/4 stick margarine. Cook slow in 275° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Add food coloring to vinegar and hot water.
Dip hard-boiled eggs until desired color is reached.
For coral, use 3 drops red and 1 yellow.
For lime green, use 3 drops yellow and 1 green. For Aquamarine, use 2 drops green and 4 blue.

title: heavenly herb jelly
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients and bring to boiling.
Add pectin.
Heat to full, rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute.
Remove leaves.
Pour liquid into hot, clean jelly glasses.
Cover with 1/8-inch hot paraffin.
Seal.
Makes 7 half pints.

title: hamburger-cheese soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add chopped onions, carrots, celery, potatoes and a little water.
Cook until vegetables are done.
In pan, combine Cheddar cheese soup, potato soup and milk.
Add hamburger.
Cook until warm.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Immediately add jello and stir to completely dissolve jello. Add water and let stand in refrigerator until it begins to jell. Add Cool Whip, cheese and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole sprayed with nonstick spray and put in refrigerator overnight. Serves 18.

title: crispy caramel treats
directions: Microwave caramels, margarine and water in 1-quart micro-safe bowl on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until smooth, stirring every minute.
Pour over cereal; stir until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool; cut into squares. Decorate with frosting and candies, if desired.
Makes approximately 24.

title: green chile burro's
directions: Remember to make your gravy from your juices!

title: mustard
directions: Mix together and let stand for 1 hour or so and then cook until thick.
Add butter the size of a walnut.
If too thick, thin down with vinegar.
This is hot!!!

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Fold all ingredients into egg whites.
Spread mixture on toast points or melba toast.
Broil until browned.

title: veggie quesadillas
directions: In a medium bowl, combine salsa, beans and zucchini. Spread 1/4 of the mixture over each 4 tortillas. Top each portion with 3 Tbsp cheese; cover each with another tortilla.

title: cabbage creole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Chop cabbage to bite-size pieces.
Mix together meat, cabbage, tomatoes, salt, pepper, onions, soup and water.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with corn bread.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into thick pieces; boil until soft.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients; mix
together.
Bake
in an oiled 2 1/2-quart baking dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Scald mixture
of
sugar,
Crisco
and	milk.
Let milk mixture cool
to
lukewarm.
Add dry yeast and enough flour to make a
batter
the consistency of cake batter.
Cover and let rise until	double	in bulk, about 1 hour.	Add baking powder, soda, salt	and
enough
flour
to	make
a soft dough.
Flour fingers and form balls of dough, about golf-ball size.
Put in greased muffin
tin.
Cover
and let rise until double in bulk again, about 1 hour.
Bake in 450° oven 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepperoni and cheese loaf
directions: Thaw
dough and allow
to
rise
according
to	package directions.
Divide dough in
half	and set one portion aside. Turn out remaining dough
on
lightly
floured
surface.
Roll into 10-inch circle.
Combine
egg	and Parmesan cheese, stirring well.
Spread 1/2 of
egg
mixture	over circle leaving a 1/2-inch margin at edge.
Lay 1/2 pepperoni and 1/2 Mozzarella over egg mixture and sprinkle
with	1/2 of oregano and basil. Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Seal
edges
and fold under ends. Transfer loaf, seam side
down,
to an ungreased baking sheet. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Brush top of loaf with egg. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut
into slices and serve.
May be served with a side of spaghetti sauce for dipping.

title: mexican creamed corn
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine corn, green pepper, red pepper, celery and 1/2 cup water.
Cook about 5 minutes or until corn is tender.
Drain.
Stir in cream cheese, chili peppers, milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings. Per serving:
3 g. fat and 0 mg. cholesterol.

title: cranberry-walnut bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift the flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Add the combined remaining ingredients, mixing only enough to moisten. Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Combine jello, sugar, boiling water, lemon juice and rind. Whip jello when it gets to syrupy stage.
Whip milk and add to jello and blend.
Roll crackers; add melted butter.
Mix and then line the bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add jello mixture.
Top with dry crumbs.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken wings
directions: In a deep bowl, mix all ingredients together except wings. Add wings, making sure they are all covered with sauce.
Marinate overnight or at least 4 hours. When ready to cook, cover cookie sheet with foil.
Spray foil with cooking spray. Brush wings with sauce.
Bake at 350` for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven. Turn and brush again with sauce. Bake another 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven. Serve.
You may also use just Kikkoman sauce and leave out the barbecue sauce.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pour melted butter over loaf.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Shape in rolls and bake until golden brown, 10 minutes at 400°.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the egg yolks with the sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in the milk, bourbon and brandy.
In a separate bowl, whip the heavy cream and in another bowl, beat the egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold the whipped cream into the yolk and milk mixture, then fold in the egg whites.
Garnish with nutmeg.
Makes 25 (8 ounce) portions.

title: easy oven rice
directions: Combine soup and butter.
Stir well.
Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add mushrooms and water chestnuts to liquid. Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and rice to soup mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour and 10 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Put over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Cook, uncovered for 3 more minutes or until liquid evaporates.
Set aside.
Combine Ricotta and eggs.
Stir well.
Divide mixture in half.
Add carrot to 1/2 Ricotta.
Stir well.
Add zucchini to other 1/2 Ricotta and stir well.
Set aside.
Put 3 lasagna noodles lengthwise in 1 layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, coated with spray.
Spread carrot mix on top of noodles.
Spoon 1 cup of spaghetti sauce over carrots. Top with 3 noodles.
Spread zucchini mix over noodles.
Spoon 1 cup sauce over zucchini.
Top with 3 noodles.
Put mushrooms on noodles.
Use rest of sauce over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in sour milk.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and stir in. Mix pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill.
Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Drop dough about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with pecan half or cherry. Makes 4 dozen.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Chill before baking.

title: coffee a la mode
directions: For each serving, pour hot strong coffee into coffee mugs to about 3/4 full.
Add scoop of ice cream and serve immediately.

title: daddy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus and remove scales with a knife or vegetable peeler, if desired.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place
in
11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish and add water. Cover with plastic wrap (heavy-duty) and microwave on High for 6 to
minutes
or
until
crisp-tender;
drain.
Cover and chill.

title: chicken broccoli casserole 2
directions: Cook broccoli. Arrange on bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole.
Layer chicken pieces (cut up) over broccoli.
Pour sauce (made from soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and Cheddar cheese) over chicken. Top with the dressing mixed with the melted margarine.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add almost a jar of spaghetti sauce.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheeses over top (as desired, a good bit).
Combine flour, egg and milk.
Pour over meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail noodles
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add butter and cream.
Stir.
Add salt and baking powder and enough flour to roll out easily.

title: herbed onion focaccia
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Roll dough into 10 X 14 rectangle. Brush with 1 tsp. oil. Slice onions. Heat 1 tsp. oil in frying pan. Add onion and garlic and cook over medium heat 2-3 minutes or until onions are soft. Evenly spread cooked onion and garlic over crust pressing lightly, sprinkle with herbs. Grate parmesan cheese and sprinkle over onion. Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares using pizza cutter.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Stir oatmeal, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Let sit until lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Stir in flour and knead.
Cover and allow to rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Stir down and make into 3 loaves, 3 x 8 x 4-inch greased bread tins.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn down oven to 325° and bake another 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients thoroughly. (I mix mine with my hands at the last.)
Then form into balls (about nickel size). Cool in refrigerator 3 hours. Mix last three ingredients in the top of a double boiler.
Dip the peanut butter balls into chocolate mixture.
Put on cookie sheet to cool.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Mix egg, vinegar and cold water and add to first ingredients.
May be refrigerated until needed.
Makes 3 to 4 crusts.

title: inez's oatmeal cookies(my family's favorite)
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Mixture will be hard to mix with mixer. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° until done.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and cottage cheese. Cut oleo and other cheeses into small chunks and mix together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the butter and cheese until soft. Add egg and water. Beat well. Sift flour, salt, cayenne and paprika together.
Add in additions, beating well after each addition.
Chill dough 10 minutes.
Pack into Wearever cooking gun (sawtooth, spritz cookie discs).
Make long strips lengthwise on ungreased Wearever cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Yields 8 dozen 3-inch straws when dial is set on thick.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and Cool Whip and powdered sugar until real smooth.
Then gradually add each of all other ingredients. Then chill.

title: shredded beef sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered roaster.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
Remove and shred with fork while still warm.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add cabbage, carrots, onions and garlic.
Cook on low for 15 minutes; then add frozen corn and peas.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage up fine.
Grind carrots up fine.
Mix together. Put mayonnaise and milk together and stir.
Put sugar in it and mix it all together.

title: nut roll
directions: Chop all the nuts.
Mix all the ingredients, except the evaporated milk, marshmallows and 1/2 the graham crackers.
Heat the milk, then add the marshmallows, stirring until they melt. Pour over the mixed ingredients; stir well.
Form into rolls; roll in the remaining crushed cracker crumbs.
Chill until firm.

title: zesty 3 bean salad
directions: Squeeze limes into a large bowl.
Stir in salsa, salad oil, chili powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Salad doesn't have to marinate or be refrigerated before serving.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour in a baking dish.
Mix fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Pour in fruit.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rice-frank-cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and green pepper.
Stir in rice.
Add water and salt; boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup. Add frankfurters and mustard.
Heat through, stirring often.
